title: zucchini boats
directions: Wash and trim zucchini.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of zucchini; save pulp.
Cook meat until browned, breaking it up as it cooks.
Drain off all fat.
In a bowl combine all ingredients, only 1/4 cup of cheese.
Toss to mix.
Fill each zucchini half with mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place by teaspoonfuls on greased sheets and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for 1/2 can of onions. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place rest of onions on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and strip with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese, set aside.
Mix pretzels and melted butter, press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Spread cheese mixture over pretzel mixture carefully over pretzel crust.
Spread Cool Whip over cheese mixture.
Chill.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add frozen berries.
Allow to set slightly.
Pour over top.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Blend in blender, then pour in bottle.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In 1-quart baking dish, combine and mix well.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, stirring occasionally unti rice is tender and bubbly.

title: peppy cheese mounds
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients with hands, gathering into a ball.
Pinch off walnut size pieces and place 1 inch apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown at 350° (15 to 18 minutes).
Remove to rack.
Store in airtight container up to 2 weeks.

title: potatoes-wild rice au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and celery in butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add milk all at once and simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in parsley, pepper and 1 1/2 cups of shredded cheese.
Combine cooked wild rice and potatoes in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour sauce over top; top with remaining cheese and bacon pieces.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, then quarter.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in a bag.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine everything except cheese.
Over medium-high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Smash with potato masher.
Pour in cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: baked onions
directions: Mix all well.
Croutons on top too if you like.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake until browned at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water and add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Drain a pineapple (save the juice for Topping).
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows to jello and let set.

title: christmas bark candy
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chips and oil at 70% power for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave 10 to 20 seconds longer or until chips are melted, stirring occasionally.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Stir in baking bits, pretzels or desired add-in.
Spread onto waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sift together dry ingredients. Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Fold in dry ingredients. Add chopped apples and nuts. Pour into pan and bake 40 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan. Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Drain.
Beat eggs and add to sausage.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, milk and mustard.
Mix well. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.
Serve hot.

title: sharon's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Combine Kool-Aid and juices in large punch bowl.
After putting about 1/2 of mixture in, add a few ice cubes and quart of sherbet.
When all is melted, add rest of punch and sherbet. Put remaining sherbet on top before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and salt.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Combine soda and vinegar; add last and beat well. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in 3 (9-inch) pans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add green pepper, onion and celery. Saute about 5 minutes or until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, bay leaf and parsley. Simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and parsley.
Add shrimp and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat thoroughly. Prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve Creole over rice. Makes about 4 servings.

title: cocoa puff crispies
directions: Place cereal in large bowl; set aside.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the butter/margarine and marshmallows.
Microwave, uncovered on high for 3 minutes; stir.
Continue cooking until smooth, stirring after each minute until melted.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill a large cake pan or attractive container 1/2 full with lettuce.
Add remaining ingredients in layers as listed, mixing the sugar with the salad dressing.
Pour over the top and cover container.
Refrigerate up to 8 hours before serving.
Serves 18.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix sugar, water
and syrup in saucepan and boil for 10 minutes, covered.
Set
off
burner
and
add 1 teaspoon maple flavor.

title: monday greens
directions: Put greens in a saucepan.
Add water according to package directions.
Bring to a boil and lower heat.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Add
sherbet
and orange rind and mix.
Add oranges. Pour into a mold.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan with cooking spray; dust with 1 teaspoon flour. In a bowl, combine 1 3/4 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine orange rind, juice and oil; add to flour mixture. Beat at medium speed of an mixer until smooth (batter will be thick). Beat egg whites in small bowl with mixer at high speed until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites into batter. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack. Yield: 16 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add taco seasoning and recommended water.
Set aside and cool.
Tear up lettuce and add chopped tomatoes, onion and shredded cheese.
Stir sugar, Thousand Island dressing and salsa together.
Pour over top and toss, just before serving.
Low calorie dressing and no sugar.
Still makes a great salad.

title: jiffy lemon pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip and dry Jello together.
Mix the instant pudding with the milk.
Combine the Jello mixture and the pudding mixture together and pour into either a graham cracker crust, crumb crust or baked pie shell.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until thick.
Serve over ham.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain well. Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: squaw bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Roll out like biscuits.
Cut in pieces about 2 inches by 4 inches.
Slit the center and fry in deep oil until golden brown.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Put the chicken breasts on bottom of large casserole dish. Peel and slice potatoes and put over chicken.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken and potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients in 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.

Cook without stirring to soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add butter. Do not stir. Cool at room temperature. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Add pecans and coconut if desired. Quickly spread in lightly greased plate.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until done.

title: potato puffs
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spread evenly in skillet and fry golden brown.
Turn with help of a plate.
Brown the other side.
Serve hot, in wedges.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat eggs. Then add the next 6 ingredients and mix well. Add salmon. Shape into 12 patties, 3-inches each. Fry in a skillet until browned on both sides. These are good baked in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and freeze.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Combine the dry cake mix with eggs, oil, buttermilk, cocoa and food coloring. Go by directions on cake box before baking. Add only the ingredients in list. Do not add the ingredients listed on the box mix.

title: apple dumplings(for 6)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Roll out pastry a little less than 1/8-inch thick and cut into 7-inch squares.
Pare and core an apple for each dumpling.
Boil next 4 ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Place apple on each square of pastry.
Fill cavities of apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot each with butter.
Bring opposite points of pastry up over the apple.
Overlap, moisten and seal.
Place a little apart in baking dish.
Pour hot syrup around dumplings.
(I pour over each one.)
Bake immediately for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with the syrup, cream, whipped cream or ice cream.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry pound cake
directions: Cut cranberry sauce into small pieces. Set aside. Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and nuts. Blend until smooth. Fold cranberry sauce into batter. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage leaves for 5 minutes. Cook butter and onion for 5 minutes. Add tomato, brown sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; set aside.

title: white chocolate chip-macadamia nut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together the butter and shortening.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Add the white chocolate chips and Macadamia nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Drop cookie dough from rounded teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Space about 2 1/2 inches apart.
Flatten top of each cookie slightly.
Bake in center of a preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly golden.
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven and let sit 5 minutes. With a spatula, move cookies to a wire rack to cool.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: chipped beef - cream cheese
directions: Mix with mixer until spreadable.
Makes 16 ounces.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: 20-minute chicken creole
directions: Spray deep skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat pan over high heat.
Cook chicken in hot skillet, stirring, for 3 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Reduce heat.
Add tomatoes and their juice, low sodium chili sauce, green pepper, celery, onion, garlic, parsley, crushed red pepper and salt.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice or whole wheat pasta.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Saute meat; pour off any fat. Put all vegetables and seasonings in a pot. Save orzo until soup has been simmering for about 1 hour. Add orzo and cook until soft. Season to taste.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple and milk in a bowl; blend with mixer.
Add Cool Whip; blend.
Add lemon juice; blend.
Pour into pie crust.
Keep cool.

title: swedish meatballs(some meatballs you'll like)
directions: Mix the
ingredients
as
you
would a meat loaf, using just enough
milk
to moisten.
Shape into teaspoon size meatballs and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bundt cake
directions: Mix:
In a large bowl, combine the margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix on low speed until blended.
(Repeat until all ingredients are blended.) Add vanilla and lemon extract flavors (blend well).
Pour batter in cake pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 3 hours (overnight is best).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine. Cook mixed vegetables per package. In large pan, boil broth and gravy mix (which is dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water). Stir until thick.
Add remaining ingredients (except biscuits).
Bring to boil. Pour into sprayed 8-inch square baking dish. Separate 4 biscuits into 8 pieces and place on top of mixture. Bake at 350° until biscuits are done and pot pie is bubbly.

title: strawberry punch bowl shortcake(good for group party)
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O; stir to dissolve.
Add the frozen strawberries; let set until it partially jells.
Have your vanilla pudding mixed according to directions.
Cut the cake layers in half to have 4 layers.
In punch bowl, layer Jell-O with strawberries, cake layer, pudding and Cool Whip.
Continue to do 4 layers.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: toffee bars
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes. Place graham cracker on foil lined pan. Pour mixture on crackers. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In 5-quart covered pan, heat corn oil over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; saute 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: spanish beans
directions: Cut onion and bell pepper in strips.
Saute in butter or oil until tender.
Add string beans and tomatoes.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Delicious served with Spanish rice and barbecued chicken.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend avocados in blender or mixer until smooth.
Add onions. Add lemon juice to keep dip from turning dark.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: In a large saucepot, heat oil. Add flour and cook over low heat, stirring often, until "roux" (roux-a flavor base for gumbos, soups, sauces or gravies.
It's a slowly cooked mixture of flour and oil.
Another name for it is Cajun napalm) turns dark brown in color and develops a nutty aroma.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender. Slowly add chicken broth, a little at a time, stirring after each addition.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, okra, bay leaf or leaves, file and the 3 peppers. Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, shrimp, hot links or sausage and crab meat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice and Tabasco sauce, if desired.
I prefer to place the rice in the gumbo for about 5 minutes prior to serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Mix milk, oil, eggs and onion and pour into dry ingredients. Cook in preheated 400° oven in 8 x 8-inch pan until top is browned (about 40 to 45 minutes).

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until soft (peeled).
Cool and mash with fork, adding powdered sugar until it has pie crust consistency.
May get watery when you start, but add sugar and it will get stiff like dough.
Roll out like pie crust until thin.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up into long strip (like you would sweet rolls). Cut into pieces about 1/2-inch thick.
Enjoy!

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand until dough is very soft.
Pat out on cookie sheet.
Brush top with unbeaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and sliced almonds.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cut in squares when warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in large kettle, salted boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
In medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and saute until onion is
tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir onion-bacon mixture into drained zucchini; add remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese and toss until well coated. Spoon zucchini into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Contains about 200 calories per 10 servings.

title: tuxedo pasta
directions: Cook pasta, drain and keep warm.
In large skillet over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and mushrooms, cook about 5 minutes or until golden brown; stirring often.
Add zucchini and bell pepper; cook about 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender crisp.
Add wine and lemon juice; simmer one minute. Remove from heat, stir in basil and remaining butter.
Add pasta and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese; toss to mix.
Place on platter to serve, sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Easy - do ahead.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Better if made the day before serving.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper, using grinder (frozen cranberries grind best).
Add sugar and chill 2 hours.
Fold rest of ingredients into berry mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours or freeze in 8-inch square glass dish and serve at a later date.

title: taco soup
directions: Note:
Do not drain any of the canned ingredients.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, beating well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, ending with flour. Beat well. Add flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes.
Let set for 1 day before eating.

title: cabbage meat skillet(one dish meal)
directions: Saute meat and onion about 10 minutes.
Pour off liquid.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes. Add cabbage and rice.
Stir together, mixing well.
Cover; continue to cook 18 to 20 minutes.

title: new zealand curry
directions: Brown beef; add onion and cook 2 minutes.
Add spices, syrup and sugar.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add water just to cover.
Cook 20 minutes; add 1/2 cup sultanas and 1/2 chopped apple and 1 bay leaf.
Thicken with flour.
Serve over rice.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: gram's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend oatmeal to make flour.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add slowly to first mixture.
Then add chips and grated chocolate. Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 375° for probably 8 minutes or so (or longer).
Don't overbake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup and peanuts to a boil. Stir constantly. Reduce heat and cook until it reaches 300°.
Remove from stove.
Add soda. (It will foam real good.) Pour into buttered cookie sheet and cool.

title: sweet bread
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Stir lightly.
Add melted lard or Crisco.
Mix well.
Roll on well floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: quick cookies
directions: In boiler add sugar and cocoa and milk and butter.
On medium heat, bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes in large bowl.
Mix peanut butter and salt and vanilla and oats; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: apple pudding
directions: Place apples in buttered baking dish.
Add water and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover with crumb mixture made by creaming together cracker crumbs, butter and brown sugar.
Bake until done.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally until forms into a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool, beat and pour in buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Saute ground beef in oil until it turns gray.
Cook egg noodles by directions on package.
Add all ingredients, except grated cheese and pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream gravy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine flour and salt.
Gradually add drippings.
Stir in wine.
Cook over medium until thickened, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in sour cream and heat through, but not to boil.
This is an excellent gravy to use with all kinds of roasts.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage into small pieces.
Boil in salt water until tender.
Saute onions in oleo; add cheese.
Allow to melt over low heat.
When cheese is melted, add soup.
Blend well.
Add strained cabbage and mix well.
Add bread crumbs until mix is a casserole consistency, about 3/4 to 1 cup.
Season to taste.
Put into a 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Brown seed in skillet over medium heat.
Cream butter, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla and sesame seed. Drop on greased cookie sheets by 1/2 teaspoons about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove to wire racks.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir mixture until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with nuts.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice
and
egg yolks together, using a mixer for 2 minutes on high speed.
Pour in cracker shell.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a
9 x 13-inch pan. Cream the butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake 5 minutes. Swirl melted chips to marbleize.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken in a packet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Partially cook the rice by halving the amount of water normally used.
On a sheet of aluminum foil, layer the ingredients in order given, beginning with the rice.
Wrap packet tightly and bake for 1 hour.

title: jack cheese and egg casserole
directions: Tear bread into chunks.
Place evenly in a shallow 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheeses (Cheddar, Jack and cream).
Top with green chilies.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and red pepper in a separate bowl.
Pour over casserole.
Chill for several hours.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: simple peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of oblong pan.
In a bowl, combine flour and sugar; add milk and stir until you have a smooth batter. Pour over top of peaches and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in saucepan in boiling unsalted water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain well.
Return to saucepan and stir in margarine.
Stir in egg and Parmesan cheese.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick coating.
Press spaghetti mixture onto the bottom and up the sides of pie plate to form crust.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
In skillet, cook beef or turkey, onion, pepper and garlic until onion is tender and beef is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and oregano. Spread meat mixture over cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings; 262 calories each.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with Cool Whip. Add pineapple, juice, nuts and marshmallows. Chill until set.

title: raisin bran cookies
directions: Crush cereal.
Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: microwave potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and water in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish; cover and microwave on High for 8 to 12 minutes, or until tender, stirring after 6 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in pan over medium heat.
When melted, add chow mein noodles and dry roasted peanuts.
Make sure noodles and peanuts are covered with melted morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with mayonnaise; add diced chicken.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Hydrate gelatin in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to mayonnaise and marshmallows while warm.
Add whipped cream and fruit; freeze.
Do not stir after putting in pan.
Use a warmed spoon or spatula to cut.
After cutting, eat immediately.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions in butter until golden.
Combine water, onions, bouillon cubes and bay leaf.
Simmer 1 hour.
Pour into bowl with slice of Italian bread.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: garlic soup
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add next six ingredients.
Boil 1 hour.
Add noodles.
Cook until soft.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time (beat well).
Sift dry.
Add flour, then bananas and then flour.
Add nuts last.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan; bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Make "well" in center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans. Spoon batter into 2 lightly greased 8-inch loaf pans.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
If you have some left over in the blender, blend a few seconds before serving again.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in canola oil.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon rice on each browned chop.
Add 1 slice tomato, onion and pepper to each chop.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water; simmer until water is absorbed and rice is done.
Add a green salad and rolls, and you have a very good meal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick. Season with salt and pepper. Coat both sides with cornmeal. Heat enough of the bacon drippings to coat the bottom of a saut pan or skillet. Pan-fry the tomatoes until lightly browned on each side.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together.
Mix the molasses and buttermilk together, then stir into the dry ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased mold and cover tightly.
Place on a rack over boiling water.
Cover the steamer and cook 2 hours.
Serve steaming hot slices with Boston Baked Beans.
If there is any leftover, reheat it in a skillet with butter.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve cranberry sauce in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and add to cranberry mixture. Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 9-inch glass pan to jell. When jelled, spread sour cream over the top.
Pour the rest of the jello mixture over the top.
Chill overnight.

title: hot brunch casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer cooked sausage, chilies, onions and picante sauce in dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine baking mix, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Gently pour over layered mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and celery, Add sauce and seasoning. Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot; add bouillon.
Stir until dissolved.
Add soy sauce and boil again.
Remove from heat; add eggs all at once, stirring rapidly in a circle with spoon.
Stir in scallions.
Serve immediately.

title: western beef and corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in the remaining filling ingredients and set aside.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on 2 packages Pepperidge Farm party rolls.
Cover and heat for 10 minutes at 400°.
Freezes well.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil until tender.
Drain. Add onion, eggs and seasoning.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until browned.
Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: hearty hash
directions: Combine meat, potatoes, salt, pepper, celery salt, parsley, paprika and milk in a large mixing bowl. Let stand 10 minutes. Saute onions in melted butter; add to meat mixture. Spread meat mixture in skillet. Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes. Do not stir. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Serve with green salad or vegetables. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 1-quart saucepan, melt butter on a simmer setting.
Remove from heat. Gradually add flour, then milk, stirring as you add.
Cook on a simmer setting, stirring frequently, until sauce thickens. Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, evenly combine corn, eggs, cheese sauce and seasonings. Top with bread crumbs. Cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Melt margarine with unsweetened chocolate.
Remove from heat; add sugar and mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well. Add sifted flour
and
baking
powder.
Add
vanilla and nuts. Pour in well-greased pan,
9 x 13-inches.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: carole's peanut butter cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Leave it in the pan and punch holes all over it with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Mix the brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt and milk in a heavy boiler and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat just enough to keep it from boiling over.
Stir occasionally. Cook almost to a soft ball stage and add the peanut butter. Continue cooking and rapidly stirring to break the peanut butter up.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour over the cake and let set for a few minutes.
Serve warm.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Add all ingredients to yolks and mash together.
Refill egg whites. Sprinkle tops lightly with paprika.

title: tarragon chicken with asparagus(207 calories per serving)
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil until hot. Add asparagus and red pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until nearly crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Add chicken and reserved onion mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken is opaque, about 2 minutes.

In a small bowl, combine until smooth 1/4 cup orange juice and cornstarch; stir into skillet along with remaining 1 cup orange juice, tarragon, salt and black pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils, 2 to 3 minutes.
Boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute longer.
Serve over hot cooked fettucine.
This dish has only 5 grams fat and 195 milligrams sodium.

title: sausage and cheese hot hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook 1 lb. of sausage in frying pan...drain.
Add 1 lb. of Velveeta cheese and heat until melted.
Scoop one tablespoon of mixture on slices of miniature rye bread.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all together very well.
Work in well the meat.
Form balls and fry.
Make gravy if you like.

title: cucumber salad (2)
directions: Mix well, pour over cucumbers, stirring once in a while. Marinate 1 hour and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine boiling water, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool; add eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into the 1 cup warm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Blend in flour. Cover and refrigerate in a large, greased bowl.
Cover with wet cloth.
Take out as needed and shape into rolls.
Allow to rise at room temperature.
Dough will keep for about a week.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: super pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels, oleo and water.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Suggest shortening and butter be softened.
Mix well.
Beat 1 egg at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients, mix well.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fully heated.
This tastes best after it has cooled some.

title: baked fudge
directions: In medium bowl, with wooden spoon, beat eggs, sugar, flour, cocoa and salt until well blended.
Mix in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, set in a pan of boiling water.
Bake 45 minutes or until it is set like custard and crust on top at 325°.
Cool 20 minutes, then refrigerate.

title: buffet slaw salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in salt, lemon juice, cold water and pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds or square pan. Chill until firm.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Place yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in dish and cover with saucer.
Let stand for 15 minutes until it bubbles.
Grease the insides of 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Add yeast mixture to dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix.
Drop in greased coffee cans (half in each).
Cover with plastic lids that come with the cans. When the lids pop off, you are ready to bake the bread in the cans without the lids.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until transparent. Add rice to skillet and cook for several minutes with onion and green pepper.
Add chicken broth, garlic salt and pepper.
Bring to boil on top of the range.
Pour in ovenproof bowl and cover. Place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove immediately.
Serves 4.

title: skillet chicken mozzarella
directions: Cut green pepper and zucchini into strips.
Slice onion.
Set vegetables aside.

title: chili cheese soup dip
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot.
Serve with your favorite chip.
This is great for fall and winter gatherings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together, except 1 package of dried beef and nuts. Shape into ball and cover with other package of beef or nuts. Refrigerate.

title: low country boil
directions: In a large cooker pot with burner, fill water about 3 to 4 inches deep.
Add salt, pepper, and seasoning.
Bring water to a boil.
Put lid on pot.
Add potatoes and boil for 20 minutes.
Add corn, sausage, crabs, or shrimp.
Bring to a second boil.
Boil this for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn off.
Let soak for as long as you like.
The longer it soaks, the spicier it will be.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In heavy frying pan on low heat, melt margarine.
Add sugar, coconut and dates.
Cook about 5 minutes and then stir in nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring.
Gently roll into small balls.
Be sure not to pack.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
You may also roll in crushed Rice Krispies, nuts or coconut.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add oil and beat.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix into egg mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cook carrots, onions and celery in water.
Melt butter; add flour and blend. Set aside.
Pour milk into pot over medium heat. Do not boil.
Add flour mixture and dissolve.
Remove carrots, celery and onions from liquid and reserve vegetables for another use.
Use 1 quart of the vegetable broth to add to the milk.
Add the chicken broth, salt and pepper and cook until the mixture coats a spoon.
Add Velveeta cheese, cut in small pieces, then add the potatoes and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: poor man's frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan over low heat; whisk until thick.
Let cool completely.
Refrigerate. Meanwhile, beat margarine and Crisco with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Add flour paste; beat 4 minutes.
The secret is the mixing.

title: midge's pudding sauce(hard sauce)
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar until smooth. Add egg yolk (unbeaten) and beat mixture well together.
Then add vanilla and 3 tablespoons boiling water, one at a time, beating well as each is added.
Fold in beaten egg white and set aside to harden.

title: low calorie pie crust
directions: Mix and pat into 8-inch pie pan and chill.

title: turkey-almond bake
directions: Prepare vegetables, following package directions, except use milk.
Combine vegetables, noodles from mix, dry sauce from mix, turkey and butter.
Add boiling water; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover, bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.
Uncover; stir well.
Sprinkle with potato chips and almonds from the mix; bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: easter fair noodles
directions: Put 1 1/2 c. flour in a bowl - make a "well".
Add 2 whole eggs and yolks of 4 eggs.
Stir with fork.
Add enough flour to knead.
Make it firm enough to roll.
Divide into 4 pieces.
Roll paper thin.
Partially dry.
Stack and cut into thin strips. Finish drying.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken.
Baste often. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook wild rice and in chicken broth until liquid disappears. Cool.
Mix together turkey or chicken, red grapes, red pepper, green onions and cooled rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Chill pie shell.
Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg yolks which have been slightly beaten and buttermilk, butter, and flavorings.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until they peak when batter is raised and then fold into custard mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle crushed pecans. Bake for 10 minutes.
Then turn oven to 325 degrees for 30 minutes until pie is golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream the cheese until light.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until combined.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use with vegetables.

title: great fruity muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oats, baking powder and cinnamon in large bowl.
Break egg in another bowl; add sugar and whisk smooth; whisk in vanilla and melted butter.
Stir in apple, raisins and cranberries.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Fold in just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into lined or greased muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown and firm to touch.
Turn onto rack and cool.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.
Do not freeze.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Sprinkle salt and then add flour to make a stiff dough.
Put on floured board and knead more flour until all stays together and can be rolled.
Roll very thin and cut into 1/4-inch strips for noodles.
Let set for about 20 minutes.
Add to broth.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
Stir when adding noodles to broth so they don't stick together.
One egg is enough for 2 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine corn and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter custard mochi
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients, one at a time, and mix well until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and cut.

title: italian pepper salad(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Char peppers by placing in broiler pan (about 6 inches away from flame).

Keep turning peppers as they become blackened. Continue turning for about 1/2 hour, until flesh is tender. Remove from oven and place in a brown paper bag until cool. Charred skin should then peel away easily.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 400° for 30 minutes.
(Fits well in Pampered Chef deep dish baker.)

title: dan's refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Boil water; add baking soda and set aside to cool.
Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs; stir in water and soda.
Add flours, salt and cereals.
Stir gradually and add buttermilk.
Add raisins, dates or nuts if desired.
Put into greased tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Keep remaining batter in refrigerator, tightly covered.
This batter keeps up to six weeks.

title: johnny bull or suet pudding
directions: Scald baking soda in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together with enough water to make it soupy, but not real thin. Put in top of double boiler (cut a small piece of cloth and put it on top before putting on the lid).
Cook all day on top of boiling water.
Serve hot or cold with the following sauce:
Cream 1 tablespoon flour and oleo; add vanilla and milk or water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over pudding.

title: fried rice
directions: Scramble eggs ahead.
Let set.
Cook rice ahead and let cool ahead while you fry your bacon until it is crisp.
Drain most of the grease, let enough in so you can saute the green onions until tender.
Gradually add the cooled rice.
Mix all ingredients together and flavor with soy sauce to your own taste.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix cake mix (omit butter), eggs and oil.
Add mandarin oranges with juice.
Bake in three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Put chicken in pan. Sprinkle garlic and 2 teaspoons butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Combine honey, soy sauce, ginger and rest of butter.
Melt together in microwave for 1 minute on High.
Pour this mixture over chicken and bake 15 minutes more.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° until brown.

title: roy's favorite beef & biscuit casserole
directions: Brown the ground chuck, drain.
Stir i the next 5 ingredients and heat until it starts to bubble.
Pour into a 2 qt. baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half to form half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375 for 25-30 minutes, till biscuits are golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Mix flour, sugar and oleo to the crumbling stage. Sprinkle over top of apples.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: ham casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole with margarine.
Alternate layers of potatoes, ham and onion slices.
In a small bowl, blend the soup, milk, salt, pepper, tarragon and parsley.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled cheese (with a twist)
directions: Spread a small amount of mayonnaise on one slice of bread. Add bacon, tomato and cheese. Put another piece on top to make sandwich.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Cook at 350° in well-greased iron skillet for 40 minutes.

title: carnival jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: dump cake
directions: On bottom of pan, put grease.
Dump cherries and pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit and pour melted oleo over the cake. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake as directed on cake mix.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Enjoy, it's very good.

title: mexican bean rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Drain salsa in colander (keep liquid).
Add taco mix, refried beans, green chilies and liquid from salsa to beef and onion mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Spoon 1/4 to 1/3 cup meat mixture in tortilla; sprinkle cheese on inside; fold up.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Top with salsa, lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes.
Easy and delicious!!

title: spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in the onion, green pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the rice is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: cream of wheat "corn" bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 425° in a well-greased pan until done.
For muffins, grease and flour muffin tins.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, celery and meat.
Saute until all red disappears from meat.
Add chili powder, tomatoes, beans, cabbage and water to first mixture and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole(serving size:  12)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, eggs last.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup butter with flour and powdered sugar just until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: my best baked beans
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Cut into 1-inch squares and stir-fry with whatever butter is left until light brown.
Mix all other ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan and place bread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients a few hours before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Place 2 to 3 tablespoons in coffee filter and make in coffee maker.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Form into balls and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together tomato soup and brown sugar.
Pour over meatballs using all of the sauce.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix eggs, margarine, sugar, vinegar and vanilla in blender and then in bowl; stir in coconut, pecans and raisins and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frozen coconut is best if you can find it.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture in melted margarine, not mixing.
Add about 1 quart berries in the middle of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. You can use any kind of fruit and you can also sweeten fruit.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together for iced tea or hot tea.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss together spaghetti, egg, butter, Parmesan and parsley flakes; set aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef, red pepper and scallions.
Cook, stirring, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Mozzarella and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all well and pour into two 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 325° until brown and firm.

title: lentil roast
directions: Place egg and onion in blender and whiz so onion gets ground up.
Slightly mash lentils; mix everything together.
Bake in oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with gravy or cranberry sauce.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Fry wonton wrappers in oil and drain well.
Mix chicken pieces, lettuce pieces and onion slices in a large bowl.
Put dressing over and mix. Right before serving, add fried wontons and mix.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients except bacon in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and mix well.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cajun rice dressing
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, pepper and celery. Saute until tender. Stir in soups. Add water, salt and rice. Bake in a 357° oven until rice is cooked, about 25 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: 1 quart dill refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash cukes and cut into halves or quarters.
Add 2 sprigs dill on top and bottom of jar.
Add tap water to fill jar.
Do not overfill, only to neck of jar.
Turn jar upside down a few times to mix vinegar, salt and sugar.
Refrigerate 24 hours before eating.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw the peas in a bowl of hot tap water for a couple of seconds.
Drain peas.
Add shredded cheese and Ranch dressing, until covered, and stir.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Peel and dice tomatoes.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, basil and olive oil to tomatoes and season to taste with vinegar and salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Boil the spaghetti and drain.
Toss hot spaghetti with tomato mixture.
Serve immediately topped with cheese.
The tomato mixture may be prepared ahead but if it is refrigerated, bring it back to room temperature before mixing with the hot spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy eggs benedict
directions: Poach eggs.
Butter and toast muffins.
Prepare Hollandaise sauce.
Place a slice of ham on muffins.
Drizzle with Hollandaise sauce.

title: banana split (dream) cake
directions: Blend cereal finely in blender. Mix cereal, sugar and melted butter. Mix well, then pack into a 12 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° to brown crust.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda and cinnamon; stir into creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve over cream cheese or accompany roast beef, corned beef or ham.

title: fudge balls
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and roll in nuts.
Leave overnight to dry.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together just until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy dutch apple cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 inch square baking dish.
Mix cake mix, sugar, oats, cinnamon and nuts and coconut if desired. Sprinkle over pie filling and pour melted butter over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan; brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Mix cream cheese and chicken, onions, Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Shape into a ball and top with green peppers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and mash. Melt butter and add to stuffing. Mix well. Save half for squash mixture. With other half, line bottom of shallow casserole dish (reserve small amount for topping). Add remainder of ingredients to squash. Mix well. Fill dish with squash mixture; top with stuffing mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of size of Pyrex dish needed for amount of chops.
Top with slice of onion and green pepper strips on each pork chop.
Add stewed tomatoes, including celery, no juice.
Can bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix all until crumbly.
Pour 1/2 into bottom of greased deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 7 to 8 cups of rhubarb on top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and line bottom of spring-form pan.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add rice and raisins; mix well.
Microwave just until thickened (uncovered), 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add cinnamon.
Fold thickened part from edge to middle. Continue cooking until set.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and let stand 30 minutes without stirring.
Serve warmed, chilled with light cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Brown meat, garlic and onions in salad oil.
Stir	in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano; cover
and	simmer	for
to
20 minutes or until slightly thickened.	Fill
casserole by alternating layers of noodles, cheese,
tomato-meat
mixture
and	Parmesan cheese. Bake in moderately	hot
oven
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour into deep casserole dish.
Make paste of flour and milk.
Pour this paste over butter (oleo).
Do not stir.
Mix chicken and broth.
Place on top of flour mixture.
Do not stir. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
(I double this recipe.)

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Wrap a bacon slice around each Club cracker.
Place on broiler pan and bake at 350° until bacon is crisp, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Take wrappers off tamales and cut into bite sized pieces. Place in a greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next three ingredients (milk, chicken and chilies) and pour over tamales.
Add chunks of chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: yankee gravy
directions: Melt fat and remove from heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth. Return to heat.
Add cold liquid all at once and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cook over direct heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into loaf pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Take 5 quarters yards of calico.

title: scalloped chicken and stuffing
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Pour over stuffing mix. Toss lightly.
Stir while adding hot broth.
Spread in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with chicken.
Melt remaining margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stir constantly.
Cool slightly.
Stir in eggs and parsley.
Pour sauce over chicken and stuffing.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: herb cornbread stuffing(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients except chicken stock.
Add chicken stock and toss until bread is moistened.
Place in nonstick baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If dressing appears dry add more chicken stock.

title: venison jerky
directions: Use no salt unless desired.

title: streusel strawberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well blended. Add egg and flour.
Beat until mixture is crumbly, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture; press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/2-inch of edge of crust. Crumble reserved crumb mixture over preserves.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salted peanut cake
directions: Beat dickens out of eggs.
Add sugar, shortening and vanilla. After creamed together, add buttermilk with soda in it.
Stir more.
Sift flour and baking powder; stir peanuts in.
Bake at 350° for one-half hour.

title: north carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Mix, beginning with dry ingredients, then adding liquids. Makes 6 quarts (enough to baste two 150 pound pigs plus enough to serve with the meat after it's been pulled).

title: darryl's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Lightly grease muffin pans with Crisco using your fingers. (Dorian liked using the large Texas-style muffin pans his grandmother bought him because they make bigger size muffins.) Preheat oven to 350°.

title: lemon instant sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and water.
Add cake mix and lemon pudding.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour a pan.
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil, remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved. Cool slightly.
Stir in Coke and fruit.
Chill until firm.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip before serving.

title: bacon & cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Save crust to feed birds or ducks.
Cut bread in half.
Spread a small amount of Cheese Whiz on each piece of bread.
Roll up tightly.
Cut each slice of bacon into 3 or 4 pieces.
Wrap the bacon around each roll and secure with a toothpick.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve hot.
If needed, you can freeze these and then reheat at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, honey and oil together.
Stir in salt, soda, baking powder, ginger and grated zucchini.
(Zucchini should be about 1 1/2 cups, loosely packed.)
Mix in flour and walnuts.
Butter and flour a loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over broccoli (cut into cubes).
Combine soup, mayo, juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread cubes and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix up 1 cup flour at a time. Save 1 cup flour to put on wax paper.
Put batter on waxed paper and knead well.
Pinch off a piece of dough about the size of a lemon, then place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 tbsp. sugar, and margarine and press into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool.

title: peanut butter and celery
directions: Put peanut butter on plate with celery sticks.
Dip celery in peanut butter and enjoy!!

title: four cheese, pasta and beef
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain.
In skillet, brown meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add tomatoes; cook uncovered until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation and Cook Time:
30 minutes.

title: cheesy star snacks
directions: Combine the flour, cheese, Baby Bam, salt and mustard in a mixing bowl. Add the butter and work it in with 2 forks or your fingers until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add the cold water and continue working with your fingers until the mixture comes together to form a smooth dough. Form the dough into a flat disk; cover with plastic wrap and transfer to the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes and at most overnight. Make sure that the oven rack is in the center position and preheat the oven to 375°. Uncover the dough; place on a lightly floured surface and sprinkle it lightly with flour. Use a lightly floured rolling pin to roll the dough out to a thickness of 1/8-inch.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in 1/4 cup water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over the potatoes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Pour over corn flakes and pour over potatoes.
Let bake 2 minutes longer.

title: lemon ice
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir sugar and water until sugar is dissolved. Remove from the heat. Stir in lemon juice. Pour into a freezer container. Freeze for 4 hours, stirring every 30 minutes or until mixture becomes slushy. Sprinkle servings with lemon peel. Yields 6 servings.

title: love punch
directions: Puree strawberries in blender or press through
coarse sieve or food mill.
Blend in undiluted orange concentrate.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide among 6 or 8 glasses.
Fill to the top with ginger ale.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs and add milk and dry mustard.
Cube bread and add sausage and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish and refrigerate overnight.
Put into cold oven and turn on to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes; until brown and bubbly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish with tortilla chips.
Mix browned beef, soups, sauce, chilies and milk and pour over chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs.
Cut the marshmallows into the cream and let stand while you roll the graham crackers.
Cut dates into cream.
Add nuts and graham crackers all but 1/3 cup of crumbs.
Mix until it can be made into a roll.
Roll it into the 1/3 cup of crumbs.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.
Do not bake.

title: olive garden toscano soup
directions: Combine the stock and cream in a saucepan over medium heat. Slice the unpeeled potato into 1/4 inch slices, then quarter the slices and add them to the soup.
Add the kale.
Grill or saute the sausage.
When cooked and cooled, cut the sausage at an angle into slices about 1/2 inch thick.
Add the sausage to the soup. Add the spices and let the soup simmer for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Melt butter and add to eggs. Beat slightly and add buttermilk.
Beat and add vanilla.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk; knead 1 minute. Add raisins.
Put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon broiled chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and brush with butter. Place on rack in a broiler pan, skin side down.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over chicken.
Broil for 20 minutes, brushing with some of the remaining butter frequently.
Turn and broil until brown and tender, brushing with remaining butter occasionally.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add crab meat, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. Microwave 2 minutes or until hot.
Serve with crackers, breads, etc.

title: frozen yogurt with kahlua
directions: Place 1/2 cup frozen yogurt in each of 4 champagne glasses. Top
with 1 tablespoon Kahlua.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion, then drain.
While this is cooking, mix together the next 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl (cornmeal mix, buttermilk, oil, eggs, corn).

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Mix lightly all except the cream and 1/2 cup mayonnaise. Put in baked pie crust. Whip the cream, then fold in remaining mayonnaise. Spread over top. Chill for 1/2 hour before serving pie shaped wedges.

title: fudge icing
directions: Put ingredients in a saucepan, bring to a full boil and let boil 1 minute.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat and beat until warm.
Poke holes in cake and pour over hot cake.

title: french bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and the yeast.
Heat 2 1/2 cups water, sugar, 1 tablespoon salt and shortening just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly to melt shortening.
Add to dry mixture.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: cracker barrel cheese ball
directions: Mix and form ball; cool until firm, then roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator about 2 hours before serving.
Remove Saran Wrap and place crackers around cheese ball.
Makes 2 small or 1 large ball.

title: english peas and almonds
directions: Saute peas, almonds and mushrooms in butter approximately 10 minutes, until done. Salt and serve.

title: mrs. clarke's favorite hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a 9-inch pie plate or chafing dish. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: chicken artichoke
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Place in large skillet with 4 or 5 tablespoons butter.
Brown on both sides.
Remove and set aside. Saute mushrooms and green onions in remaining butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over and stir in chicken broth and sherry.
Add more flour to make a gravy consistency.
Add artichoke hearts.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add chicken and cook 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with your favorite pasta.

title: pork and beans
directions: Brown meat and onions in small amount of oil.
Mix with other ingredients except bacon.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Arrange bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May cook on top of range, stirring constantly.
"The best."

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Soften margarine and cheese; mix well.
Add flour; work into ball.
Add Tabasco.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll small balls. Flatten on cookie sheet with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: easy kid's taco-mac
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground turkey until crumbly.
Blend in taco spices and seasonings, tomatoes, water, pasta and celery. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. In medium bowl, combine corn muffin mix, egg and milk; stir with fork just to mix.
Place meat mixture in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon dollops of corn muffin mix on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add malted powder, molasses and salt.
Stir in flour and caraway seed. Knead about 5 minutes.
Cut into 12 pieces.
Shape into a long rope and then a pretzel.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Moisten lightly with water.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 pretzels.

title: beef ball
directions: Grind dried beef in food processor or blender. Set aside. Soften cream cheese, add all other ingredients. Mix some of the chopped beef into this mixture. Keep enough beef to roll the cream cheese mixture in. Shape into a ball and serve with crackers.

title: marinated broccoli and dip
directions: Mix in large Ziploc or sealed container with fresh, cut up broccoli.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Then add prunes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cut cake in squares while hot.
Pour icing over cake while cake and icing are both hot.
While cake is baking, prepare topping.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Brush on meat as it cooks.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: You will need jelly jars.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Makes about 4 to 6 sandwiches.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix, beating well, and chill about 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream and strawberry and banana slices.
Line the bottom and sides of 3 1/2-quart glass serving bowl with pound cake slices.
Next spoon pudding and fruit mixture onto cake slices.
Garnish with strawberry and banana slices.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: davy crockett bars
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda and mix in brown sugar, oats and chocolate chips.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into chocolate chip mixture.
Press into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and vanilla wafers into casserole dish.
Mix together the milk, egg yolks, flour and 1 tablespoon vanilla. Cook until thickened.
Pour over bananas and wafers.
Beat egg whites and add sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over pudding and brown slightly.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, vanilla, eggs, milk, salt and margarine well.
Put in a greased baking dish.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions and 1/2 dried beef and seasoning.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining chipped beef. Serve with crackers.

title: lemony light cooler(makes about 7 cups)
directions: In pitcher, combine wine, sugar and ReaLemon brand; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda and fruit; serve over ice.

title: heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Whip Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add and stir well each fruit, one at a time.
Be sure and drain fruit well.

title: pepperidge farm meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In a large bowl mix onions and remaining ingredients.
Form into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Then pour 8
ounces tomato sauce over meat and sprinkle with 1 tsp. crushed oregano and bake 20 minutes more.

title: cotton picking cake
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients.
Pour into three well-greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: molly's pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fish or clam chowder(new england style-white)
directions: Cook potatoes in water in a covered saucepan until tender. In another pan, saute onions, mushrooms and pepper in oil or butter until onions are golden.
Slowly add flour to vegetable mixture, stirring gently but constantly, to coat all vegetables. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until smoothly blended.
Add fish or clams, salt, pepper and tamari or soy sauce.
Cook, covered, on medium heat for 15 minutes or until fish is tender. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add parsley, sherry, cooked potatoes and potato water.
Heat through and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(Best when made several hours ahead of time.)

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix crumbs, pecans and butter; press firmly into bottom of 9-inch springform pan. Bake 8 minutes. Cool slightly.

title: creamed crab meat
directions: Mix and heat the first four ingredients.
Add the rest. Serve on toast, noodles or rice.

title: harriet's nut pies
directions: Line muffin tins with regular pie dough.
Blend remaining ingredients and fill pie shells.
Bake about 25 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: buckeyes
directions: Butter and peanut butter should be at room temperature.
Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth; roll into balls.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler. Use toothpick to dip balls into chocolate 2/3 way covered. Let dry on foil. Makes about 175. Let them set 1 hour before picking up.

title: western barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 3 hours at 275°.
Use as needed or freeze the rest.
May substitute ham for bacon.

title: ground chicken dumplings(low carb replacement for flour dumplings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, form into balls the size of large marbles and refrigerate for several hours. Cook in simmering broth or salted water for 10 minutes.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Early in day, mix beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, eggs and milk.
Shape into balls and place in shallow pan (pour shortening on bottom of pan).
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 350° until onions are tender (45 to 60 minutes).

title: grandmother frances mcatee's special sugar cookies
directions: Roll very thin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
(Use a floured pastry cloth.)
Cut into cookie cutter shapes.
Bake in oven at 350° and be careful not to burn.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by small spoonfuls (these really rise) on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Place pretzels and butter in 13-inch pan; bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over top of lukewarm pretzels.
Spread whipped topping over cheese. Chill.
Dissolve jello in boiling pineapple juice.
Stir in strawberries and allow to thicken to jelled point.
Spread over topping and refrigerate until firm.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with spaghetti sauce mix. Pour in the can of whole tomatoes.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with cooked spaghetti noodles.
Serves 6.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine sugar, butter and peanut butter in a large mixer bowl. Beat until mixture is well blended and begins to cling together. Roll mixture into 3/4-inch balls and place balls on waxed paper.

title: crab ala bob schewennsen
directions: In frypan, saute mushrooms in butter.
Add chicken stock and simmer 15 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except onions and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add onions.
Add cracked crab and cover for 15 minutes.
Remove crab into large bowl, placing in oven to keep warm and thicken gravy with cornstarch, as desired.
Pour sauce over crab and serve.

title: old fashioned taffy
directions: Boil all ingredients until the hard ball stage.
Pour into greased pan or greased marble slab to cool.
When cool enough to handle, pull
until white.
This was used for the old fashioned taffy pull.
Especially fun for young people.
The longer it is pulled (to get air out of it), the better.

title: japan vegetable rice
directions: Wash, trim and chop the leeks.
Peel and finely chop the ginger.
Peel and crush the garlic.
Heat the oil in a wok or wide pan.
Add the leeks, ginger and garlic.
Fry gently for 5 minutes. Add the rice and stir for a few minutes.
Add the water and the salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the greens to the pan.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to 235° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir and put in greased pan.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix together the nuts and flaked coconut.
Put this mixture on bottom and sides of pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix about 30 seconds until mixture is moist.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 1 hour or until cake tests done and is golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Punch holes in hot cake while still in pan.
Pour half of Coconut Sauce mixture over cake.
Cool cake completely.
Remove from pan and pour remaining Coconut Sauce mixture over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and flaked coconut.

title: pecan pie(microwave)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup in medium bowl using a rotary beater.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Microwave 15 minutes on 8 or until filling is set, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
Let cool, covered with foil, for 15 minutes.

title: lemonade chicken
directions: In skillet saute chicken until pink is gone; saute in 2 tablespoons olive oil and
2 cloves garlic.
Add lemonade, 1/4 cup water and bouillon; boil
until 1/2 the water is gone over medium heat.
Add peppers;
cook
minutes,
covered.
In a separate bowl, mix 2
teaspoons
cornstarch and 1/4 cup water. Stir until blended.
Add the
mixture
to
skillet; boil for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: no name salad
directions: Mix gelatin, marshmallows, cream cheese and hot water.
Beat until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Add carrot and pineapple.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip and chill.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl at the same time.
Start in a cold oven at 350°.
Done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit syrup(low-fat topping for pancakes and waffles)
directions: Cook ingredients, stirring constantly, over medium-high heat, until thickened.
Serve warm or cold.
Has 0 g fat.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Use liquid of oranges and/or pineapple for 1 1/2 cups cool water.
Add to jello mixture.
Add sherbet, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Mix all together.
Put cut-up banana on top with Cool Whip before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the lard and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed. Add buttermilk and then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Roll and cut out cookies.
(If batter is too soft, refrigerate until it's a little solid.)
Bake at 400° until very lightly brown.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Place oatmeal in a large mixing bowl.
Add the coconut, wheat germ, seeds and nuts.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Brown pork chops and onion in a large skillet, coated with cooking spray.
Combine water, bouillon granules and pepper, stirring to dissolve.
Add to skillet.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Add apple slices and cinnamon to mixture in skillet.
Cover and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Transfer to a serving platter and serve hot.
Yields 4 servings of 1 chop with 3/4 cup apples.
Calories:
182. Exchanges:
1 1/2 starch; 1 medium-fat meat.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain and spread in baking dish. Mix cheese, onion and soup and pour over cabbage.
Mix bread crumbs with melted oleo and cover other ingredients.
Bake until bubbles or golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender; drain.
Combine soup and cream; mix well.
Place cabbage in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and top with soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Top this with Ritz crackers and oleo that have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 hours or on high setting for 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
(Makes 1 1/2-quarts.)

title: nutty popcorn 'n wheat munch(makes about 8 cups)
directions: In large greased heat-proof bowl, combine cereal, popcorn, walnuts and raisins; set aside.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli in 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe pan.
Mix soup, sour cream, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Stir in chicken.
Pour over broccoli.
Set aside.
Melt butter in microwave for 50 to 60 seconds.
Stir in cheese; add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 12 to 14 minutes or until hot.

title: ritzy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 2 or 3 minutes, just until hot through; drain well.
Cut up, if needed.
