Cube cheese and 1 stick oleo into casserole dish with the broccoli.
Stir until oleo and cheese begin to melt.
Crush roll of Ritz crackers; mix with 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Put on top of broccoli.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; bake 10 more minutes.

title: party boston baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 30.

title: frosty strawberries
directions: Crush cookies into fine crumbs.
Set aside 1/4 cup of crumbs. Mix remaining crumbs with melted butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Press into pan and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Use an electric mixer to beat egg whites, sugar, lemon juice and strawberries for 15 minutes on medium speed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread strawberry mixture over cookie crust in pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup crumbs over top.
Freeze overnight, covered. Serve frozen.

title: chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken in teriyaki sauce overnight.
Cook chicken slowly in fresh sauce for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool chicken, slice it very thin and cut into pieces about 1-inch long. Mix all ingredients together for salad.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in a bowl.
Melt and bring to a boil the cocoa, hot water and shortening.
Add to sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch greased cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Ice while hot.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef; then add all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours until thick.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce-fudge brownies
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brownie mix, water, egg and applesauce in a large bowl.
Beat by hand, 50 strokes. Don't undermix.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Check brownies for doneness at 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Store in covered container.
Sinful yet sensible eating.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine vanilla crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour half batter evenly over prepared crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife gently swirl through batter to marble.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill in refrigerator a couple of hours.
Cut in bars.

title: "3" step cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still warm, puncture top entirely with a fork.
Spread Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Cool and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: hot pepper sauce
directions: In large pot, cover bottom with cooking oil.
Add cut-up peppers and onions.
Cook until soft.
Drain off oil.
Add skinned tomatoes.
Let cook about a half hour.
Add tomato paste.
Cook until desired thickness.
Fill hot pint or quart jars.
Wipe rims; use hot lids.
Check seals when cool.

title: miniature meat loaves
directions: Mix and shape into large patties (oval shaped).
Quick fry and arrange in baking dish.
Pour Franco-American beef gravy over plus mushrooms.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and beef pizza
directions: Help mom make pizza crust according to directions on box.
Set aside in warm place.
Have an adult fry ground beef.
Grease a pizza pan and with your hands, spread out pizza dough.
Add pizza sauce.
Next, take a handful of beef at a time and place on top of sauce, then add ham pieces.
Put cheese on the top of pizza (however much you want).
Bake according to directions on box.

title: marshmallow sauce
directions: Mix creme and juice together and serve over fresh pineapple slices.

title: sweet cheeks bar-b-que sauce
directions: In large capacity blender, add all ingredients and blend. This sauce will separate, just shake up the container and enjoy. Keeps very well under refrigeration.
Very good on pork.
If heated, the sauce will be darker and thinner, but the taste remains the same.
Also serves as an excellent marinade.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and wrap in shells.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (line bottom).
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over shells.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Peel onions and slice in thick slices.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
In greased casserole, arrange layers of onions, bread cubes, cheese and sauce.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: spanish creme
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of the milk.
Heat remaining milk to scalding.
Pour hot milk over well beaten egg yolks and put back in the pan with sugar and salt.
Cook gently until slightly thickened, about 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Cool a bit, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Pour into a dish or mold and chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add cocoa and food coloring to mixture.
Add flour and soda, milk and vinegar alternately. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 2 greased and floured round cake pans.

title: muffin mix
directions: Boil water and add soda.
Cool.
Mix rest of the ingredients and add cooled water and soda.
Keep in the refrigerator overnight before using.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Batter will keep in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Mix everything in a bowl.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Remove and top with crushed potato chips or crushed corn flakes.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus juice;	add
water
to	juice to make 1 cup. Combine asparagus
liquid,	sugar, lemon juice and salt; bring to a boil.
Soften
gelatin
in
vinegar;
stir into hot mixture to dissolve.
Add
all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9 x 12-inch oblong dish and chill until it sets.

title: sue's tomato ham ring(friend of makay)
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Combine soup and remaining water and heat.
Combine gelatin and cheese and add to diluted soup.
Cool.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Place in ring mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce and garnish with deviled eggs.
This is a make-ahead luncheon dish for 6 to 8 ladies.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Mix red cinnamon candies in hot water.
Add all other ingredients.
Sugar may be added.
May be served chilled if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine together and pour over peaches (will be crumbly).
Bake it approximately 30 minutes or until brown in 250° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 275°. Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a pan.
Add 1 1/2 cup stuffing.
Stir until butter covers the stuffing.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake 20 more minutes or until light brown.
If 1/2 stick margarine doesn't cover crumbs, you can add more.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring milk, sugar and marshmallows to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and stir until creamy and loses its shine.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil raisins and water for 1 minute and set aside.

title: microwave fiesta rice
directions: Combine vegetables and water in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook, covered, on full power 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.
Add beef.
Cook on full power 4 to 5 1/2 minutes, or until meat is not pink.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, on full power 5 to 7 minutes until heated through.

title: claudia's broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Grate cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: scarlet sipper
directions: In a large pitcher, stir together the cran-apple drink, orange juice and lemon juice.
Slowly pour the carbonated water down the side of the pitcher and stir gently.
Serve in wine glasses. Yields 8 servings.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Boil together margarine, cocoa and water.
Let cool 1 minute, then add to flour mixture. Mix well.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: deviled scrod
directions: Wipe scrod with damp cloth and cut into 4 portions.
Combine green pepper, onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and lemon juice.
Melt butter or oleo; stir in bread crumbs.
Add to vegetable mixture; mix well.
Season scrod to your taste; dot with additional butter or oleo.
Place on foil-lined broiler rack with surface about 4-inches below source of heat.
Broil 5 minutes. Remove from broiler.
Turn scrod; top with bread crumb mixture. Return to broiler for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 1 minute.

title: pink stuff
directions: Drain pineapple (drink juice).
Mix pineapple and Eagle Brand. Add cherry pie filling; add Cool Whip.
Chill or freeze.

title: quick cassoulet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread bread crumbs on baking sheet and bake for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally until crisp and lightly colored; set aside.
Meanwhile, in Dutch oven or flameproof casserole, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions, carrots and garlic; cook, stirring, just until beginning to color, about 5 minutes.
Add kielbasa and cook, stirring until it is lightly browned, 5 minutes longer.
Add chicken or turkey, beans, tomatoes, chicken stock, wine, thyme, salt and pepper; bring to a simmer.
Sprinkle cassoulet with reserved bread crumbs and place in oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned and bubbling. Serves 6.

title: blueberry surprise(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed until partially smooth.

title: cheesy breadsticks
directions: Grease pan and preheat oven at 425°.
Take a biscuit; flatten it out and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese in the middle.
Roll up the biscuits so that none of the cheese is exposed, pinching the ends. Do the others.
Sprinkle garlic salt on it.
Bake for about 5 minutes or until golden (checking constantly).
Flip and sprinkle garlic salt and cook for 5 minutes or until golden.
Best if dipped in warmed Ragu spaghetti sauce.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add milk, salt and vanilla flavoring. Pour in pie crust. Sprinkle butter on top. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350°. Bake until brown. Let it set out for about 15 minutes for cooling.

title: milk and honey white bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk. Add honey, butter, salt and 5 cups of flour; beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft-ball of dough. Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 or 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl and grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch down and shape into loaves. Place in greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 2 loaves.

title: shoney strawberry pie
directions: Cut tops off strawberries and stand upright in pie shell.
(If using bananas, you can slice the bananas and put one layer on the bottom.)
Cook remaining ingredients on low heat, stirring constantly.
When thick and glossy, pour over strawberries and refrigerate.

title: play and munch necklace
directions: You will need a string of yarn.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, melted oleo, egg yolks, brown sugar, salt, spices and extracts.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites; add granular sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold beaten egg whites into potato mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream and orange zest.
This is a great pie!

title: pepperoni pizza
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Salt and pepper.
Spread over the 2 pizza dough circles.
Place pepperoni slices on the crusts.
Top with cheese.
Bake according to directions for crusts.
Serves 12.

title: cheese rolls or ball
directions: Cream the two cheeses together and add remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Mix together and roll in ground pecans.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil over low heat.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with the cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed fish
directions: Place fish in shallow baking pan.
Salt and pepper.
Cover the fish with cream.
Place in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Use sauce for gravy.

title: stir-n-roll pastry
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup, but do not stir.
Then pour this all at once into flour.
Stir lightly until mixed.
Divide dough in half. Place one half between 2 sheets of waxed paper, 12-inches square and roll out gently until circle reaches edges of paper.
Peel off top paper and place pastry, paper side up, in pie pan.
Peel off top paper.
If you wet the counter you are rolling the pastry on, the paper will not slip.
Makes enough for 2 pie shells or one 2-crust pie.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except pecans until thoroughly mixed. Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool and glaze.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans.

title: pancakes
directions: Heat skillet on low heat.
Combine all ingredients, stir with a wire whisk until large lumps have disappeared.
Pour slightly less than 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, that's large.
To make small pancakes, like Hank's, drop spoon drops of pancake mix.
Turn pancakes when the pancake bubbles up.

title: honey cake
directions: Cream butter and honey well.
Add eggs (beaten), buttermilk and flour sifted with soda, spices and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 layers in slow oven at 275° for about 30 minutes.
Watch closely for honey cake burns easily.
Can use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomatoes, in jar; shake well. Pour over halved cherry tomatoes.
Chill for several hours.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with crackers or chips. Garnish with sliced olives.

title: sugar free blackberry cobbler
directions: Boil berries and sweetener with plenty of water.
Make crust and put in bottom of pan
Add berry mixture on top of crust and cover with another layer of crust.
Bake until crust is brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, water and cinnamon in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Slice apples into pan.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar, the flour, salt and oleo until crumbly.
Pour over apples.
Pat smooth.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until blended. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Bake in 3 layer pans for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar in double boiler.
Stir in 1 cup boiling water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup boiling water.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Add butter and vinegar.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue, sealing to edge.
Bake at 400° for several minutes, or until brown.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple including syrup, pepper and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and cornstarch.
Mix well; add diced chicken and heat thoroughly.

title: french quarter steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Cut into serving size pieces. Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat steak in flour. Reserve excess flour mixture.
Saute onion and green pepper in hot oil in a large skillet.
Remove vegetables and set aside.
Brown steak on both sides in remaining oil.
Add vegetables, rice, tomatoes and water.
Sprinkle with reserved flour mixture.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter bars(great for the youngsters)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease bottom only of a cookie sheet. Mix egg, butter, sugars and peanut butter in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In separate bowl mix dry ingredients together, then slowly add into wet mixture while stirring.
Once mixed, spread over cookie sheet.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes or until firm.
Cut into bars and cool.
Makes about 24 to 30 bars, depending on size.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into small pieces.
Add bacon bits, raisins or grapes, sunflower seeds, celery and onions. Mix together.

title: herb butter
directions: Cream together until blended well.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Dry chicken.
In large bowl, combine next 8 ingredients.
Put chicken in and let stand overnight.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Simmer onion in Mazola oil.
Mix tomato paste, water and sugar until dissolved.
Put spaghetti into pan and add all ingredients together.
Pat top with oil.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't cover.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all items together (except soda crackers) and pour into buttered dish.
Crush soda crackers.
Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
This cooks any size roast; brown on the outside and pink on the inside.
Put roast in pan and coat with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover the top of roast with pats of butter.
Place in preheated oven, uncovered, for 5 minutes per pound.
Do not open oven door!
When roast has cooked for 5 minutes per pound, turn off oven and leave for 2 hours.
Don't open oven door until the end of this time. When this is done, you'll have a beautiful roast and plenty of au jus gravy.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out pulp; reserve shells.
In a large mixing bowl, combine potato, cottage cheese, chives, salt, pepper, onion and butter.
Beat until fluffy, adding enough milk to desired consistency.
Fill shells.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until thoroughly hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: punch(good)
directions: Mix all ahead if desired.
Add sherbet just before serving. Then ice block.

title: pollo loco (chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate chicken halves serveral hours.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter.
Add milk, water, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in an unbaked pie shell.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening and margarine together.
In a large bowl, mix melted shortening and melted margarine, sugar, eggs, cinnamon, soda, molasses and flour.
Mix well and let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
In a small saucepan, add 1/2 cup water to the raisins.
Simmer until they soften.
After the mixture is rested, add oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from spoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: lo-cal candy kisses
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line two baking sheets with aluminum foil. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in small mixer bowl until foamy.
Beat in brown sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy (do not underbeat).
Fold in crackers and orange peel.
Drop meringue by tablespoonfuls 1 1/2-inches apart onto baking sheets.
Bake 10 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave meringues in oven with door closed at least 8 hours. Remove from oven; finish cooling away from draft.
(Four dozen confections, less than 50 calories for three.)

title: caesar salad
directions: Put in a large wood salad bowl.
Sprinkle bowl with cheese, salt and pepper, garlic and beaten eggs.
Blend together.
Layer lettuce in bowl with garlic and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over salad and toss.
Let stand 10 minutes, then toss prior to serving.

title: lump crab and corn bisque
directions: Saute until clear the first 5 ingredients in a soup pot.
Add the next 6 ingredients and stir over medium/high heat until thickened, but do not boil.
At the last minute, add crab, corn, salt and pepper.
Serve hot, garnish with crab claws.

title: mount hope tea
directions: Steep tea bags; add lemonade, sugar and enough water to make 1 gallon of tea.

title: half and half cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Use for carrot sticks, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: deviled crab cakes
directions: Deep oil fry or shallow pan-fry after forming mixture into cakes.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls.
Pour tomato juice over meatballs.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine; mix with other ingredients.
Bake in casserole 1 hour at medium temperature.

title: crisco pie crust(for 2 double crust 9-inch pies, or 4 single crust pies)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together in a bowl. Cut in shortening and blend.
Beat egg, vinegar and water together and work into flour mixture.
Roll pastry into a ball and divide into 4 equal parts.
If making one double crust pie, wrap two balls of pastry in plastic and freeze for a future pie.

title: 1920's lindenberg sweet relish
directions: Run vegetables through a food chopper; add 1/2 cup salt.
Let it stand for 2 hours, then drain.
Mix with vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
This requires no cooking and does not have to be sealed.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Slice thin and line an ungreased 9 x 12-inch glass pan closely together with one roll of cookie dough.
Cookies should be touching each other.
Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs until creamy.
Pour this layer over cookies. Slice second roll of cookie dough and layer again over mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onions in heavy skillet with oil.
Add chopped tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally about 30 minutes.

title: chinese-style shrimp in pastry shells
directions: Mix chicken broth with cornstarch and teriyaki sauce.
In a large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add snow peas and green onions; stir-fry until almost tender-crisp.
Add shrimp, and stir in chicken broth mixture; cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and just comes to a boil and shrimp turn pink.
Serve in warm pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fish in almond butter
directions: In 2-quart glass baking dish, combine nuts and butter. Microwave, uncovered, for 5 minutes at High until light brown. Stir in lemon juice, wine, dill and salt.

title: sparky dip
directions: Melt and mix all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) oblong pan.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix all and enjoy.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Then mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almond slivers on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs real good.
Melt margarine in pan and pour in mix.
Put in unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie is done on top.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until meat falls off bone, then remove bones. Combine rice, carrots, onions and celery; add chicken.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Chop up all ingredients (except chips) and put into a bowl.
Add chop meat and mix well.
Add salad dressing and 1/2 bag of chips.
Mix well!
Put the rest of chips on the top to decorate!
Enjoy!!

title: lulu's luscious lumpy logs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until spoon bends.
Remove spoon and mix with hands (make sure they are clean first).
Roll into logs approximately 2 to 3 -inches long.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: texas orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix cottage cheese and jello. Add oranges and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place by teaspoonfuls on well-greased pan.
Place maraschino cherry half on each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat milk and cream cheese until creamy and smooth (beat several minutes).
Add 1/2 carton Cool Whip and beat very well. Add vanilla.
In cake pan put layer of vanilla wafers and top with sliced bananas.
Cover with pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Top with crumbs.

title: greek olives
directions: Slit olives 3 times lengthwise.
Soak olives in cold water to remove bitterness.
Change water daily.
(Let soak until you can eat one.
Some bitterness will remain.)
Next, soak olives in brine for 3 days, being sure to saturate water with salt.
Drain olives, saving brine.
Place olives into large vat.
Throw in a generous amount of oregano and pour in enough olive oil to saturate them as you turn them over and over and over.
Have jars ready.

title: cinnamon breakfast apples
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pare apples and chop into bite-sized pieces.
Put in a 4 cup measure sprinkling with cinnamon mixture, as you add apples.
When you have 4 cups, put apples, water and butter into a saucepan.
Cover and cook over low to medium heat, stirring once or twice, for 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender.
Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line bottom of baked pie shell with 1/2 of the strawberries, sliced in half.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the remainder of the whole berries and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes. Combine cornstarch and sugar and add to berries, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture is clear.
Add lemon juice.
Cool slightly and pour over the berries in the pie shell.
Chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening; then add yeast mixture and milk.
Mix well. Makes a large bowlful.
Will keep 7 to 10 days if kept in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Wash
and
slice thinly the sweet potatoes.
(Important as you slice
the potatoes, place them in water.) Heat margarine,
then add sugar.	Add sweet potatoes (drained) and cook over
medium heat until desired consistency, usually about 30 to 45
minutes. You
might	desire	to add cinnamon to taste. Nice variation for sweet potatoes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, juice and eggs together.
Blend very well.
Add Cool Whip and beat with mixer until very creamy.
Pour into vanilla crust.
Chill.

title: mary's snack mix
directions: Melt candy coating per package instructions.
Mix all together.
Spread out on wax paper.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in canned tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and the eggs; set aside.
Overlap 3 tortillas in bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Overlap 6 tortillas around sides of dish.
Spoon beef mixture evenly over tortillas; top with remaining 3 tortillas.
Spoon cheese mixture over beef and tortillas.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese mixture is set.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle remaining onions down center of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Just before serving, arrange tomato and lettuce around edge of casserole.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: beef and beans casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Fry bacon, crumble and add to meat.
Mix all other ingredients together in a rectangular baking dish.
Add meat and bacon.
Stir all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Soak apricots in boiling water for a half hour; cool to lukewarm. Grind the soaked drained apricots, peel from a half an orange, and raisins. Blend or sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

Add ground fruit; combine to coat the fruit. Make a well in the center. Add beaten egg, orange juice, water mixture and vegetable oil or melted shortening. Mix only until combined. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Let stand 20 minutes. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.
Roll Roast in peppercorns and season with pepper and garlic if desired.
Place in baking dish and bake 5 to 6 minutes per pound.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in a 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Pit and quarter dates.
Add soda and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Blend in egg.
Add flour and date mixture alternately.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: patio beans
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 375° or 400°.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Beat eggs together well with the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cheeses, butter and onions.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Add mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream remaining butter.
Gradually add remaining sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Makes 16 servings.

title: ham quiche
directions: Bake pastry and let cool.
Combine eggs, milk, pepper and baking powder.
Beat well.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Add green pepper and onion, if desired.
Spoon into shell and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm in center.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and bake in 2 round pans. Cool cake. Prepare jello with 2 cups boiling water, stirring until dissolved, then add strawberries. Prepare pudding as directed on package. Have Cool Whip thawed. Place 1 layer of cake in punch bowl. Pour 1/2 of pudding over this layer (pudding will run over sides). Over pudding, pour 1/2 of jello mixture. Cover this with 1/2 of Cool Whip. Place second layer of cake on Cool Whip and repeat steps.

title: no bake cookies
directions: *Add 3/4 cup chopped nuts or use crunchy peanut butter for variety.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix together sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Add cheese and crackers.
Pour over top melted margarine and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo ice cream delight
directions: Crush Oreos and line dish (bottom only) saving about 1/4 cup for topping.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top, distributing as evenly as possible.
Freeze for 15 minutes.
Add softened ice cream, spreading evenly, and place in freezer for a minimum of two hours, overnight preferably.

title: golden twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut lengthwise.
Slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out potato, leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Combine potato (from scoop), 1 cup cheese, salad dressing, milk, egg and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.
Fill shells.
Top with remaining cheese, onion and bacon. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place all ingredients in a roaster with a tight lid.
Bake for 3 hours.
Do not peek during baking!

title: broccoli casserole with water chestnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the last two. Top with the crackers and margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Put ingredients in pot.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 10 minutes.

title: tropic macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheets.
In medium bowl, combine mix, egg yolks, pineapple and coconut.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until edges are golden.
Makes 30 to 36 cookies.

title: berry-mallow-yam bake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Lightly toss 1 cup crumbs mixture with yams and cranberries.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and broil until lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: jailhouse rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Mix potatoes, sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Add yeast and blend.
Place in a greased bowl and cover with a damp cloth.
Store in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, take out, roll flat, cut and place in greased pan.
Let rise.
Cook at 450° until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla sugar, then mix in flour, oil and baking powder.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes at high speed.
Grease Bundt pan.
Put in 1/2 of the dough.
Peel and slice apples into small pieces; place in pan.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and then cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 20 minutes, then remove from pan.
When cold, you can sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Cook the eggplant in salted water until tender. Drain and mash. Sift flour and baking powder. Add beaten egg, butter and baking powder mixture to eggplant and mix well. Drop into hot oil and fry until brown. Yields 6 small fritters.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix up real good with spoon.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes. Take out, stir and add raw peanuts (room temperature).
Stir.
Set back in microwave for 9 minutes (taking out every 3 minutes and stir).
After 9 minutes, take out and add butter or oleo, vanilla and 6 to 8 drops red food coloring.
Stir until it loses its gloss (not too long), then drop by the spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hash browns deluxe
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Top with dry parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in margarine and remove from pan.
Saute onion and celery in browning pan.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Place chops in 9 x 13-inch pan or Dutch oven, pour 2/3 cup water over, then sauce.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in sugar mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan.
Melt butter and mix with remaining sugars.
Pour over biscuits and bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven or until done.
Best eaten warm.

title: vegetable beef soup(minestrone di carne)
directions: Place meat, bones and water in an extra large saucepan. Cover and bring to
boil.
Reduce
heat
and skim surface with slotted spoon.
Add all the rest of ingredients except for the mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Let
cook
3 hours on a medium low heat. Add
mixed
vegetables and potatoes;
cook an additional 45 minutes.
Taste
for
salt
and
pepper;
adjust
to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jaws
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
As jello begins to thicken, add fun fruits.
Let completely set.
The sharks will look like they are swimming in an ocean.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients really well.
Fold in pineapple, maraschino cherries (cut up and drained on paper towels), bananas and nuts.
Pour into mold and freeze.

title: shirley's caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/4 cup sugar.
Add oleo, and 1 cup sugar; mix well. Add evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil, add remaining sugar.
Let boil until soft ball forms when drop falls in cup of water. Remove from heat and beat with a mixer for a few minutes beating in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: macaroni chicken surprise
directions: Mix salmon, potatoes, onion, egg and pepper until blended. Form into 8 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Spread crumbs on wax paper.
Gently press patties in crumbs to coat.
Heat oil in skillet (large, nonstick).
Add patties and cook over medium heat about 4 minutes per side, until heated through, golden and crisp. Serves 4. Per serving:
344 cal., 23 g. pro., 19 gr. car., 20 g. fat, 89 g. chol., 717 mg. sod.
Exchanges 1 1/4 starch/bread, 2 1/2 medium fat meat and 1 1/2 fat.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and oatmeal well with first mixture.
Push half of the mixture down hard on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a jar of raspberry jam on top of mixture.
Push remaining mixture down on top of jam.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend
sugar,
oil,
butter and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking soda
and	cinnamon.
Mix and add carrots and vanilla. Pour
into greased
and
floured
13 x 9-inch or into two 9 x 2-inch	pans. Bake
at
325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix by hand.
Roll into small balls and press down with fork. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cookies should be real light on bottom.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: browned rice
directions: Saute onions in butter in pan.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in uncovered pan at 350°.
Stir occasionally while cooking. Serves 4.

title: grandmother's cranberry salad
directions: Freeze and grind cranberries.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and pour over cranberries.
Grind apple and add to mixture.
Add oranges, pineapple and pecans.
Stir. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set.

title: mother's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until well blended.
Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Stir in Cool Whip.
In a large glass bowl, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture until all is used.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes, turning once after 10 minutes, or bake for 7 minutes on each side and freeze.
To serve, thaw and bake for 10 minutes until brown.

title: hamburger-crouton casserole
directions: Form all ingredients into balls and brown.
Put into a casserole dish.
Pour 2 cans cream of mushroom soup over.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first six (6) ingredients thoroughly and pour in buttered dish.
Mix the next four (4) ingredients with a fork and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Spread in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Heat 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve with hard crackers.

title: quickie banana pudding
directions: Prepare Whip 'n Chill according to package directions. Alternate layers of bananas and wafers in dish; pour Whip 'n Chill over top.
Chill for 1 hour.
Yields 5 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: *Use to your liking, more or less if you want.

title: rhubarb surprise pie
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix egg and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange rhubarb evenly over the pastry.
Sprinkle the Jell-O over the rhubarb.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: May substitute 2 teaspoons of garlic salt for garlic powder and salt.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a hard boil and thicken to spreading consistency with powdered sugar.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine meat, water chestnuts, eggs, bread crumbs, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch meat balls.
In a large skillet, brown meat balls, a few at a time.
Remove from pan and pour off fat.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients except for parsley; mix well.
Pour into skillet.
Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Reduce heat and add meat balls.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: corn casserole bread
directions: Stir together and bake in a glass pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; add to milk gradually.
Add beaten egg yolks and margarine.
Cook over low heat until thick. Add coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue and coconut.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; put in casserole dish.
Melt butter by mixing it with the cooked broccoli.
Mix soups and Cheddar cheese with broccoli.
Then mix in the croutons.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: "moo's" easy dessert
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and eggs with wire whisk.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Cook raspberries and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Pour on top of pie.
Cool 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip; garnish with raspberries. Store in refrigerator.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Add beef; mix well. Shape into two patties.
In medium skillet, cook patties 4 - 5 minutes per side.
Remove to platter and keep warm.
In same skillet, saute mushrooms in butter.
Stir in flour; blend well. Add water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened. Return patties to gravy and cook uncovered over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with mashed potatoes. 2 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Drain thawed crabmeat; mix with cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour seafood cocktail sauce over all. Spread on crackers.

title: walnut delights
directions: Mix well and put into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie(easy)
directions: Heat together chicken, cream of mushroom and Veg-All.
Place crust in pie pan.
Pour heated ingredients into pie pan.
Top with second crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Preparation:
The chunkiness of this salad will depend on whether you plan to serve it in lettuce bowls (chunky) or on croissants as a sandwich spread (less chunky).
For sandwiches, chop chicken in food processor and vegetables and fruit should be diced very small.

title: squash puppies
directions: Drop by teaspoon into hot oil (375°) until brown; drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: citrus jerk orange roughy
directions: Sprinkle both sides of fillets evenly with seasoning, press gently to adhere. Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil, and place over medium heat until hot. Add fillets; cook 3 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Remove from skillet; set aside, and keep warm. Add marmalade and remaining ingredients to skillet. Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute. Pour sauce over fish. Serve immediately.

title: stuffed yeast bread roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Roll out loaf on floured wax paper (not too thin).
Brown ground meat, onions, bell peppers, and mushrooms.
Season to taste.
Drain.
Layer cheeses and meat mixture on rolled out dough.
Bring edges together in center. Place on lightly greased pan, bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix milk and soup and pour mixture on top of chicken.
Put dressing mix over this chicken mixture.
Pour chicken broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: grandma's sponge cake
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and water on high speed.
Gradually add sugar, then flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into yolk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Grate cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add Worcestershire, garlic salt and cayenne pepper to cheese and cream together.
Add chopped pecans.
Form into a ball or roll into logs.
Sprinkle paprika and a little chili powder on wax paper and roll the cheese ball/log until completely covered.
Wrap in wax paper (and tinfoil to freeze) and refrigerate.

title: trisha's french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Blend for 30 seconds. Refrigerate.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Add to apples and mix. Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and put on apples and pat firmly.
Bake until brown and apples are soft.
Serve warm with milk or cold with whipped cream.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix together well. Chill and serve.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter and garlic.
Cook and drain broccoli. Add broccoli to mushrooms.
Add soup.
Add cheese.
Stir well. Simmer on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with fresh veggies or chips.
Serve in a fondue pot or chafing dish.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters gently in butter with salt, pepper and paprika until edges of oysters begin to curl and are plump.
Add hot milk and serve at once.

title: tamale bites
directions: Combine cornbread, 1/2 cup enchilada sauce, salt and ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a small saucepan, heat together tomato sauce and remaining enchilada sauce. Serve cooked meatballs topped with heated sauce and shredded cheese.

title: picnic cake
directions: Pour water over dates and let cool; add soda and stir well. Cream together in other bowl shortening, sugar and eggs; add date mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (be generous). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable-beef soup(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 12 to 18 hours (high setting for 4 to 6 hours).

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Mix tomato paste, water, bay leaves, chopped mushrooms, garlic and salt.
Add to meat mixture and simmer.
The longer it cooks the better.

title: taco noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer and add spaghetti sauce.
Layer cooked noodles, hamburger mixture and cottage cheese (optional).
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown.

title: elegant potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil the potatoes in jackets and shred on medium grater.
Melt butter in small pan and stir in bread crumbs. Set aside.
Grate cheese.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of potatoes and cheese. Sprinkle with salt. Pour unwhipped cream over the potatoes.
Top with cheese layer and buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: luna salad(a quick and easy side or main dish)
directions: Heat pecans on low in a pan with sugar.
Stir constantly until sugar melts.
Let cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together with the pecans.
Add vinaigrette right before serving.
Amount of each ingredient depends on your taste.

title: peanut butter topping for ice cream
directions: Cook flour, cocoa, sugar and water together until thickened. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one bowl raisin coconut cookies
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, cinnamon, sugar and egg whites in large bowl.
Beat thoroughly with mixer or rotary beater.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto well-greased and lightly floured baking sheet. Leave 2 inches between each cookie.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Cookies do not brown much.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store airtight.
Yield:
about 40 cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon; put aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Place 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half the chocolate chips and 1/2 of the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Repeat with batter, chips and cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen and served later.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix together balance of ingredients.
Add to chops in frying pan.
Simmer for 30 minutes, covered, on low heat.

title: garlic cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, water and cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and seasonings; brush over hot rolls.

title: cranberry snap
directions: Stir red hots in hot water until melted. Cool and add cranberry juice and concentrates. Stir to combine. Makes 18 (5 oz.) servings.

title: heavenly potato casserole
directions: Grease casserole pan.
Mix all together except Parmesan cheese.
Put in greased casserole pan.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ginger boyda's wild rice
directions: Wash wild rice in cold water.
Simmer, covered in 2 cups water for 50 minutes until soft.
Brown sausage and drain.
Brown onion in sausage drippings.
Add mushrooms and saute briefly.
Combine in greased casserole.
Heat broth.
Combine flour and milk and stir into casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Make syrup of 3 cups sugar and 2 cups water.
Add frozen juices to the syrup and stir well.
Add red food coloring if you desire.
Add 4 quarts ginger ale before serving.

title: honeyed apricot biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly coat large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray; dust with flour.
In small bowl, whisk together egg whites and honey until well blended; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, anise, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in center and add egg white mixture and apricots.
Mix until dough is smooth and combined, about 1 minute.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 2 hours before serving so that it can become slushy.
Put in punch bowl and add 2 quarts of well chilled ginger ale.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: *Save juice and add enough water to make 1/2 cup.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar and cornstarch 3 minutes in the boiling water. Take off the stove and add the jello. Stir and cool.
Pour over the hulled strawberries, which have been placed in the shell. Cool for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: lemonade
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 cup water and lemon juice.
Add remaining cold water.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups.

title: easy egg casserole
directions: Break bread up into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over bread.
In a separate pan, brown sausage and drain.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add sausage to bread/milk/egg mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top with onion and green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake one hour at 350°.
Great Sunday brunch item.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain thoroughly.
Mix meat and onion mixture with soups and picante sauce; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.

Add water, cover and simmer for 1 hour. In a small pot, combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice (drained from pineapple chunks) and soy sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce into pot with hot pork.
Add green peppers, onion, water chestnuts and pineapple chunks.
Cook about 10 more minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: tasty corn casserole
directions: *May substitute 1/2 teaspoon salt for Molly McButter and Mrs. Dash.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind onions, cabbage, tomatoes, green and red peppers and sprinkle with salt.
Soak overnight and drain.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Boil 1 1/2 cups of sugar, butter, 2 tablespoons of cinnamon and water for 1 minute.
Mix together 3/4 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters one can at a time.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar and place in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over each layer.
Spoon a few tablespoons of the boiled mixture over each layer and pour the rest over the last layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes (very important).
Turn onto a plate.
Eat like a monkey!

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into 1/4-inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool completely.
Melt chocolate bits as package directs.
Stir in vegetable shortening, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Chill until set.

title: ham apple pie
directions: In casserole alternate ham slices and apples sprinkled with sugar.
Sprinkle top layer with lemon juice.
Cover with bread crumbs (buttered).
Bake covered for 15 minutes in a 375° oven . Uncover and bake another 26 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Warm in 300° oven.
(May also heat in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds.)
Combine soy sauce, sugar, lemon juice, cornstarch and crushed pepper.
Spray skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Stir-fry onion, sweet peppers and garlic over medium heat, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add oil to skillet.
Stir-fry turkey over medium-high heat, 3 to 4 minutes or until no longer pink.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add sweet pepper mixture.
Heat through.
Spoon onto tortillas.
Roll up.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease well 18 muffin pan cups.
Preheat oven to 375°. Measure and stir first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.

In a separate bowl, beat eggs and all other ingredients. Add egg mixture to flour mixture and stir until flour is moistened. Spoon into prepared muffin pans and bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm.
Makes 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and pull apart into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles until done.
Cut cheese into cubes and mix with hot noodles and chicken.
Then add cream of chicken, cream of mushroom and Ro-Tel.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs(very good with smoked ribs)
directions: Lace ribs on spit accordian style and secure with holding forks.
Adjust on rotisserie above drip pan.
Let ribs rotate over slow coals.

title: a quick luncheon dish
directions: Empty hash into a shallow pie plate or dish.
With a silver spoon, make 2 round wells in hash.
Break eggs into wells and dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Cook in a slow oven at 325° until eggs are firm.
You can also dress this up with a sprinkling of grated cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Serve with a canned peach half filled with mincemeat on lettuce as a salad.
Voila!
A wonderful lunch in a matter of minutes.

title: velveeta spanish rice
directions: Bring water to boil in saucepan.
Stir in ingredients, except tomato and green pepper; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir with fork until blended; cover.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine the first
5 ingredients. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan 55 minutes
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out.

title: chewy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Add pecans, raisins and oatmeal.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Drop spoonfuls of dough about the size of a walnut.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Season and brown roast.
Cook until done. Shred roast into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes or until mixture is thick.
Serve over toasted buns.
Yields 12 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate for 24 hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook meat and onion in skillet until tender. Drain fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture. Spoon into peppers.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a baking dish, add corn, eggs, sugar, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix butter in as last ingredient.
Place in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chili beef
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper with garlic, chili powder, cumin seed,
red pepper, until tender.
Stir often.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and cheese.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: punch
directions: Mix liquids and chill.
Put ice cream in punch bowl after liquid.
Best to let ice cream soften a bit.
Double or triple recipe as needed.

title: quick and easy biscuits
directions: That's all the ingredients you need.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine rice, water, pineapple juice and salt in saucepan. Mix just until rice is moistened.
Bring quickly to a boil over high heat, uncovered, fluffing rice gently once or twice with a fork (do not stir, cover).
Simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix according to directions on the box.
Pour over the chicken mixture and bake in 350° oven until cornbread is golden brown.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Simply mix together and pour on meat as it cooks.

title: old-fashion lemonade
directions: Place water, rinds and sugar in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cover; bring to a boil and simmer until rinds are tender.
Cool and remove rinds.
Add lemon juice and chilled water.
Stir briefly.
Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer first 6 ingredients for 10 minutes, then add orange juice.
Drain off spices.
Add some red coloring, if desired.
You can also put orange slices on top for garnish.
Should serve 30 to 40 people.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Lightly brown meat in a large skillet on medium high heat (drain).
Add noodles.
Drop cottage cheese evenly with spoon over noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese, spaghetti sauce, parsley flakes and salt.
Cover skillet.
When steam appears, turn heat to the lowest position.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top, return cover and let stand on warm until cheese melts - about 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl and add oil and water.
Stir with fork until holds together.
Makes double crust.
Moisten table and roll between wax paper.

title: dave's banana blueberry muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Ad the melted butter and the blueberries.
Combine the dry ingredients and stir gently; add to banana mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peanut butter-fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough evenly into an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes until done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Spread gently with cream cheese and sprinkle evenly with fruit, coconut and marshmallows.
Bake another 8 minutes until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat butter in large heavy saucepan.
Add onions and cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir in broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Place bowls on cookie sheet; put chunks of bread in each bowl and pour in soup.
Top with cheese slices.
Place under broiler about 4 minutes or until cheese lightly browns.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter. Add 1/2 the white chocolate and cover.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add to mixture.
(It's okay if the chocolate is not all melted.)
Add flour and walnuts.
Blend in remaining white and dark chocolate.
Place foil on a cookie sheet with sides and pour on batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: apple banana bread
directions: Sprinkle the apples with a little lemon juice.
Add mashed bananas and mix well.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and beat well.
Stir in apples and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients, add flavoring.
Add to apple/banana mixture.
Spoon onto 2 greased and floured loaf pans to bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk. Add vanilla and pineapple; blend well.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand a few minutes before removing cake from pan.

title: ham delight
directions: Mix all ingredients except croutons and butter.
Turn into a buttered casserole.
Top with croutons and dribble the melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and pour into mixing bowl. Add all the rest of the ingredients to bowl and mix. Pour into a serving bowl and chill until ready to serve.

title: quick beans
directions: Combine pork and beans, brown sugar, onion, catsup, molasses and pepper in 2 quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until onion is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: red cabbage and bell pepper slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, water, sugar, salt and mustard.
Simmer 3 minutes in open saucepan.
In a large, heavy skillet, heat the oil until hot but not smoking.
Add mustard seed and saute until they begin to pop.
Stir in cabbage.
Saute 1 minute.
Stir in pepper and saute 1 minute.
Add vinegar mixture and simmer for 1 minute. Drain vegetables in sieve over a saucepan.
Transfer vegetables to bowl.
Boil liquid until it reduces to about 3 tablespoons.
Stir into vegetables.
Chill, covered, overnight or 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine rice, beef, onion, salt, crumbs and paprika.
Mix. Form into balls about 1 1/2 inches diameter.
Mix soup, green pepper, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat balls in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done. Check while baking so sauce does not dry up.

title: cranberry jello sauce
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Set aside.
Add orange juice, sugar and cranberry sauce.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix jello with water and then add frozen berries.
Stir until berries soften and jello thickens. Gently pour or spread mixture on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: nyce goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
In a separate pan, cook celery, green pepper and carrots in water to cover, 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 10 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until heated through.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Cook diced potatoes in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and mix with onions.
Heat bacon fat or butter in an 8-inch skillet and add potatoes and onions.
Fry, bringing up from bottom with a spoon or spatula now and then to ensure even cooking.
Season to taste with paprika, salt and pepper.

title: lima bean cake
directions: Soak the lima beans overnight in water.
Peel the next day. Put peeled lima beans in a pot with water and boil until tender. Drain.
Put in 2 cups sugar and mix well.
Put into refrigerator until cold.

title: spinach cheese souffle
directions: Cook spinach; add cottage cheese, salt and nutmeg.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold through mixture and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops with apples and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops and onion in nonstick ovenproof skillet or Dutch oven, about 4 minutes per side.
Add sauerkraut, apple slices, apple juice, sage and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes, until chops are no longer pink.

title: spring vegetable ring
directions: Scrub potatoes.
With a vegetable peeler or sharp knife, remove a thin strip of peel around center of each potato.
Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and the water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 12 to 16 minutes.
Let stand, covered, while cooking beans.
Place remaining butter in a large shallow bowl.
Microwave on High until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
Remove cover and surround with cooked potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best oven hash
directions: Lightly mix beef, potatoes, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Mix corn flakes and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Pass catsup and mustard.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Set aside chicken to add last.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place
onion
in
chicken
cavity
and	boil in 1-quart salted water with bouillon cubes.
Remove and debone, reserving
liquid. Cook
spaghetti in liquid by bringing to a boil. Add
spaghetti and
bring to a second boil.
Cover and remove from
heat.	Leave until
all	liquid	is
absorbed.
Mix
in remaining
ingredients and stir until cheese melts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: tiny ham stuffed tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tops from tomatoes.
Remove pulp.
Drain shells, upside-down on paper towel.
In small bowl, combine deviled ham, sour cream and horseradish.
Spoon mixture into pastry bag with medium rosette tips.
Fill tomatoes with ham mixture. Refrigerate.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pasta a zucchini
directions: Take sausage out of skin and break up.
In skillet, brown sausage, onions and oregano.
Scrub zucchini and slice thin; add to skillet when sausage is half done.
Cook until zucchini is soft.
Boil water for ziti following package directions; drain. Mix ziti and sausage mixture together.
Top with grated cheese.

title: baked corn
directions: Line deep dish with pastry.
Add corn to fill dish; season with salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Cover with top crust.
Put hole in center.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in saucepan. Bring to a boil; cook until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Combine the vegetables in a salad bowl; mix lightly. Pour hot dressing over vegetables; toss lightly.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Drain 1/2 of marinade from salad before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry sausage and onion, breaking sausage into small pieces, until sausage is brown.
Drain.
Drain sauerkraut and squeeze dry. Add to sausage mixture with 1/4 cup bread crumbs, cream cheese, parsley, mustard and salt and pepper.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Place flour in a shallow bowl.
Place eggs and 2 tablespoons water in another bowl, beating lightly to combine. Place bread crumbs in
a third shallow bowl.
Shape sauerkraut mixture into small balls.
Roll in flour, then in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Fry balls, a few at a time, in deep fat heated to 375° until brown.
Drain on paper towels, then transfer to baking sheet with sides and bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen balls.

title: heavenly dip
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours.
Makes a great dip for vegetables and chips.
Makes a great sandwich spread, too!
Serves a lot!

title: aunt callie's cherry pudding cake
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons butter and egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix baking powder with flour, then add to mixture. Mix just until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, combine water, cherries (with juice), 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bring to a boil and pour over batter immediately.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until cake and pudding reverse positions and the cake springs back to a light touch.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in unbeaten egg; stir in molasses and orange rind.
Blend in dry ingredients and then chill overnight.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook meat in skillet until light brown.
Sprinkle taco seasoning and add other ingredients.
Stir and cook a little while; then pour over taco chips in a baking dish and bake.
Then cover with grated cheese.

title: pirouette pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add melted chocolate and
gradually add eggs, one at a time.
Beat each egg 1 1/2
minutes.
Pour
into	pie
shell
and
chill. Prepare pudding as directed on package and pour over chocolate layer. Chill for 2 hours.	Garnish with whipped cream and add chocolate curls.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Mix;
let
stand 3 to 4 hours.	Cook on low temperature until thickened and seal.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preparation time:
About 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield: 2 medium sized loaves.

title: orange sherbet dessert
directions: Crush cookies and fold the cookies and nuts into Cool Whip. Spread half of mixture in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread softened orange sherbet over this.
Top with the rest of the cookie mixture and freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put ingredients as listed into a bowl; mix.
Put eggs in, one at a time; blend each one.
Put the nuts in by folding, not mixing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in ungreased tube pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add last three ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix milk and egg in a bowl.
Dip chicken in mixture and cover with bread crumbs.
Brown rapidly in oiled skillet and place in baking dish.
Add 1/2 bottle of dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can make gravy with drippings from pan. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: fabulous apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat for 5 minutes and add eggs one at a time.
Continue to beat well until combined. Add dry ingredients mixing well.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts. Bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 16 - 20.

title: classic cooked eggnog
directions: In a large saucepan, beat together eggs, sugar and salt, if using.
Stir in 2 cups of the milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and just coats a metal spoon. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining 2 cups of milk and the vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, pour into a bowl or pitcher.
Serve immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cream butter, cheese and milk until smooth.
Add corn and mix.
Pour in well greased 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Flatten bread.
Combine rest of ingredients and spread in bread; roll up.
Dip in melted butter.
Slice in thirds and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 425°.
May be frozen before being baked.

title: easy-does-it spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and place in crock-pot. Add all remaining ingredients except dry spaghetti. Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (high 3 to 5 hours).
Turn on high the last 1 hour and stir in dry spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: perfect pineapple punch
directions: In a large container, mix all ingredients then pour punch into freezer bags. Freeze. Thaw until slushy before serving. Place into punch bowl and pour ginger ale over. Stir and serve. Makes 20 servings.

title: potato boats
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper and celery.
Drain fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop out and reserve shells.
Mash potatoes and mix with meat; fill shells. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook in a large pot, all ingredients except meat.
On medium heat, brown meat; stir in meat with ingredients in pot.
Turn down heat to low; cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally until done.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in bottle.
Cover and shake well before using.
Makes 3/4 cup.
Keep in refrigeration when made.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Save 1/4 cup of drippings.
Cook onion in the drippings until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of water; cook until thickened.
Stir in bacon, potatoes and eggs.
Better if let stand overnight.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve warm with taco chips.
If I use the hot salsa, I leave out the red pepper.
I also melt cheese a little in microwave.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, 30 seconds. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean, about 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or applesauce.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add salt, oil and sugar, then pour over yeast. Add flour and mix well.
Knead a few times and roll out on a floured surface.
Cut out rolls and brush tops with butter.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl combine sugar, water and yeast.
Dissolve and let set for 10 minutes, then add milk, eggs and salt; mix well. Add flour, knead until dough don't stick to hand.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Make rolls; let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Use flour on hands and dough to make rolls.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: candied carrot yams
directions: Cut carrots in large chunks; cook.
Drain; add milk, butter and brown sugar.
Let simmer for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion.
Add soups, chilies and chicken. Line casserole dish with Doritos or corn chips.
Add layer of chicken mixture, 1/2 pound cheese (grated) and another layer of Doritos or corn chips.
Alternate until all is used.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: honey-apple pancakes
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt, apple pie spice and baking soda.
In small bowl, stir together egg, apple juice, honey and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring until blended, but still slightly lumpy. Pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, greased griddle.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges.
Turn and finish cooking.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 8 or 9-inch pie pans. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over layers. Refrigerate for day and night, if possible.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Chill ingredients before mixing.
Mix in punch bowl, using ice cream scoop to add sherbet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and margarine.
Add soup, water and eggs to casserole dish.
Add cooked broccoli.
Add cheese and rice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Cover with paprika and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: party bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour and baking soda onto wax paper. Mix brown sugar and butter in a bowl until crumbly. Stir in flour mixture, coconut and oats. Press firmly into a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar until blended.
Cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir in.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake until when touched lightly with finger only a slight imprint remains.
Do not overbake.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit cake - old fashion country cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in jam and preserves.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: rotel style tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook slowly until thick. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal. Use in recipes calling for Ro-Tel tomatoes or serve as a dip with chips or tacos.

title: canned poke using vinegar
directions: Wash tender poke.
Add to boiling water.
Boil until wilted. Drain poke.
Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Cook until done or soft. Put in jars and seal.

title: cold water dills
directions: Fill quart jar with pickle-size cucumbers and add salt, garlic and dill.
Fill with water.
Let set 1 week before eating.

title: chinese barbecue sauce
directions: In a food processor, mince garlic and ginger.
Add rest of ingredients and blend well.
Store in a glass jar in refrigerator. Keeps indefinitely.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar; add egg.
Sift flour with salt. Add flour alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add coconut, lemon and vanilla flavoring and pudding mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and Karo syrup.
