Stir while cooking until sugar melts.
Cook until it forms a ball when a little bit is dropped in cold water.
Set in pan of cold water to cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered pan and cut into squares when hardened.

title: turtle cake
directions: 1. Prepare cake mix as directed on pkg adding 1/3 c. of the evaporated milk. Put half of this mix in a 13 x 9
pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
2. Meanwhile melt caramels and 1/3 c. evaporated milk. Add
nuts.
3. Pour caramel mixture over cake. Add chocolate chips,
then top with remaining cake mix. 4. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in the butter.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into slices.
Combine other ingredients, beating together just until all dry ingredients are well moistened.
Coat onion rings well with batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil at 375°, turning once with fork.
When onions are golden, drain on paper toweling, then sprinkle with salt.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put apples into greased 1 1/2 qt. shallow baking dish.

blend flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt with butter or margarine to a mealy consistency; sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 to 40 min. or until apples are tender and topping is slightly crusty and brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 2 eggs, 1 at a time, then 1 cup flour; add other eggs, 1 at a time.
Add the second cup of flour and then the flavoring.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 325° in a preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: oven baked eggplant
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside. Check with fork.

title: carameled corn
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, butter and salt for 5 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole lightly with oil.
Cook mushrooms and peppers in oil until peppers are tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix broth with milk.
Add slowly to flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in chicken and pimento.
Mix in spaghetti.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly throughout, about 30 minutes. Makes 4 (1-cup) servings, 375 calories per serving.

title: turkey salad burritos
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine turkey, celery, onion, black olives and cheese.

title: boneless chicken
directions: Marinate overnight.
Drain, flour and deep fry.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix all but soda and cook until it forms a hard ball in water.
Stir in soda well.
Pour over popcorn and form into balls. Makes about 12 balls.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine cake mix and spices in bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and 1/3 less water than called for on cake mix box.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Glaze with toppings of your choice.

title: chili frank round-up
directions: In saucepan, brown frankfurters and cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Arrange cheese in lattice shape on top of casserole.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put in saucepan. let simmer, but do not boil.
Bake meat until tender, then pour 1/2 dip over meat.
Let simmer in oven approximately 10 minutes.
Serve remainder of dip with meat on table.
Keep leftover dip in refrigerator but remove lemon slice.

title: ed's delicious cinnamon swirl cookies
directions: Place graham crackers in a food processor and grind until desired consistency.
That's it.
Can be used as topping on cereal, oatmeal, sundaes, etc.

title: pam's chicken dip
directions: Shred chicken and mix with other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with jumbo corn chips.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube cake pan. Preheat oven to 325°. Mix cinnamon and sugar. Roll quartered biscuits in sugar and cinnamon and layer biscuits and nuts. Mix brown sugar, butter and orange extract. Bring to quick boil and pour over layered biscuits and nuts. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Mix 10x sugar with just enough water to drizzle over cake.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a microwavable dish.
Microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Rotate dish and microwave for 4 minutes or until fully cooked.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: crab dabs
directions: Drain crab meat; remove any shells or cartilage.
Chop crab meat.
Combine all ingredients except bacon; mix thoroughly. Chill 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Put 1/2 of batter in prepared 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
While cake is in oven, melt caramels.
Add evaporated milk and melted margarine. Pour over baked cake.
Spread pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel.
Pour remaining batter over the top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except last 2) together.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Excellent served with brisket!

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all the vegetables, seasonings, tomatoes and water together in a soup kettle.
Wash rice and sprinkle over top of liquid.
Place the soup bone in the kettle.
Cover kettle.
Bring to steaming point, turn to low heat and cook slowly for about 3 hours or longer, if that fits in better with your plans.
When ready to serve the soup, remove the soup bone and add to soup the little particles of meat that might be clinging to it.
The bits of meat make a richer soup.
The soup is then ready for serving. Serves 8.

title: newman's ritzy chicken
directions: Add lemon juice to Paul Newman's dressing.
Marinate chicken in this mixture at least 2 hours. (Overnight is best.)

title: smooth lemon pie
directions: In a large heat resistant bowl, dissolve your gelatin in boiling water with a wire whisk.
Stir in yogurt, and fold in whipped cream with a wooden spoon.
Pour mixture in the pie crust. Spread whipped topping on the pie.
Refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Makes 8 servings.
3 points per serving.

title: ravioli style filling(for manicotti)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Set aside to cool.
When cooled, put in bowl and mix with all other ingredients.
Stuff cooled shells with filling.
Put half of the sauce in baking dish.
Lay filled pasta on bottom. Add rest of sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: divinity
directions: Place syrup, sugar and water in heavy saucepan and cook over low
heat.	Stir
only
until
sugar
is dissolved.
Cook until syrup
mixture
reaches
soft ball stage.
Check this by dropping syrup
into ice water.
Beat egg whites on high speed until stiff. Continue beating egg whites and pour off half of syrup
(soft ball
stage)
over egg whites.
Continue cooking remaining half of	syrup
until
it
forms a hard crack.
Add remaining
syrup and
vanilla.
Beat
until	mixture is stiff enough to spoon onto wax paper.

title: quaker lace cookies
directions: Combine oats, melted oleo and salt.
Combine sugar and baking powder together and pour over oat mixture, blending with a fork. Add beaten egg, then nuts and vanilla.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil, drop small amounts of mixture on sheet at wide intervals as they spread.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Watch closely, they burn easily.
Let cool on foil before removing. Keep crisp in airtight container.

title: "cholesterol-free" shrimp cocktail
directions: Steam or microwave cauliflower (pulled apart somewhat) until shrimp consistency (steaming about 5 minutes).
Rinse immediately in cold water.
Break cauliflower into bite size when cool. Arrange on serving platter.
Combine remaining ingredients as low calorie cocktail sauce, taste it and you will think you are eating shrimp.

title: chocolate raspberry bars
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over very low heat.
Cool slightly. Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in butter, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Turn into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.
Spread top with jam and sprinkle with chocolate while warm.
Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: beef ala stroganoff
directions: Trim all fat and gristle from steak.
Cut meat into small cubes.
Drain mushrooms, saving broth.
Chop into small pieces. To cook, heat 2 tablespoons butter or drippings in large frying pan.
When hot, add cut up beef.
Cover.
Brown and cook slowly for 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add mushrooms to beef and cook 10 minutes longer.
Push mixture to one side of pan; add sour cream, stirring.
Add meat mixture and mix well.
Add salt and paprika to taste.
Cover and simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Serve on top of toast, torn into bits.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix small amounts of Cool Whip into cream cheese until both ingredients are blended.

title: cranberry-baked apple(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, stir cranberry sauce, raisins, cinnamon and orange peel; set aside.
Core apples and pare a 2-inch strip from top all around.
In a 9 or 10-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam, place apples.
Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice over each apple and fill with mixture, letting excess fall into pan.
(Can be microwaved, uncovered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes.)

title: finnish corn bread
directions: Scald the milk and mix in the sugar, butter, salt and cardamon seed.
Melt the yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water and pour into milk mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour while stirring mixture. Knead dough until it no longer sticks to hands and let it rise until double in bulk.
Divide dough into 3 parts and knead into long rolls.
Braid the rolls and fold each end under to make it secure.
Place in greased pans and let rise until double again. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When taking the bread out of oven, brush 2 tablespoons coffee and 3 tablespoons sugar over warm bread. It may also be frosted.

title: green bean and bacon casserole
directions: Take 8 to 10 green beans.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around beans; fasten with toothpick.
Place in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Pour Catalina French dressing over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bacon is brown.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square pan on the bottom and sides.
In a bowl, sift flour.
Add baking powder. Melt margarine over low heat; stir in brown sugar until well blended.
Add egg and vanilla; stir well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts if used.
Spread in a greased pan.
Bake in center of oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm, cut into strips.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add to macaroni. Mix together mayonnaise, soup, cheese and pimento.
Put in a casserole and bake at 300° until quite hot.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, drain. Mix with other ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°

title: italian beef pie
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain well.
Cook and drain spinach. Combine meat, spinach, sour cream, soup and season to taste.
Pour in oiled 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.

title: guilt free snack chips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut tortilla into eighths.
Spread on baking sheet lightly sprayed with cooking spray.
Using a pastry brush, brush salad dressing over tops of chips.
Sprinkle with garlic salt or herb blend.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool completely before storing in airtight container.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cover pecan halves with egg white mixture; then dip in sugar mixture.
Bake in shallow pan at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: curried squash and pear bisque
directions: Cut the squash in half and discard seeds and membrane.
Bake in conventional oven at 375 for 45 minutes or in microwave for about 10 minutes.
To microwave squash add small amount of water and cover with plastic wrap.
After cooking, remove squash pulp from skin.

title: italian-style hot dogs
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil until hot, stirring frequently. Cook onion, pepper, garlic and wieners until vegetables are tender and wieners are heated through.
Spoon wiener mixture into toasted hot dog buns!

title: cajun rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly brown meat and drain. Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour. (More jalapeno pepper or hot sauce may be added for more "fire".)

title: spinach tortellini casserole
directions: Cook tortellini until done.
Drain and mix with tomato and basil.
Mix milk with spinach and add to tortellini mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix oleo and sugar.
Add chocolate and eggs (one at a time) and mix well.
Add vanilla and flour and mix. Bake in greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep in covered jar.
To serve, stir 1 heaping teaspoonful in 1 cup boiling water.

title: pizza
directions: *Hamburg, sausage, black olives, onion, pepperoni, etc.

title: market day stew
directions: Cube meat into small chunks.
Coat meat with flour and soup mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add as much water as you think needed.
Season.
Put in 350° oven for 1 hour, then turn down oven to 325° or 300° and leave in oven for 2 or 3 hours.

title: jubilee jumble cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend in nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
While warm, glaze with 2 tablespoons oleo. Beat in 2 cups powdered sugar and 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Add coconut (small amount).
Heat oleo until golden brown.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in pan to bake.
Pour on remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put about 4 tablespoons of batter per greased cake pan.
Continue until all 14 layers are made.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water until done. Drain. Mash, leaving some chunks. Fry bacon and set aside to cool. Saute onions in bacon grease. Crumble up bacon and place in pot with potatoes. Add onions, milk, salt and pepper and butter. Warm on medium heat, being careful not to scorch. Serve with saltine crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put over fettucine or boiled fish fillets.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and saute onion until golden.
Add meat and brown thoroughly.
Add sauce and salt.
Heat through.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut and work together, as you would a pie crust (takes a little time).
Form into balls and bake on greased cookie sheet at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.
Delicious-can make days ahead.

title: laurie's chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Brown in hot oil (2 tablespoons). Remove chicken from skillet. Blend flour, thyme and onion into drippings. Cook 2 minutes.
Add wine, catsup and chicken (skin side down).
Cover and cook 25 minutes. Add celery, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
Prepare rice with chicken bouillon cube dissolved in water. Serve chicken on rice.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Blend egg and milk.
Coat chops in crumb mixture.
Dip in egg mixture and again in crumbs. Place in dish in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chops and bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to
packaged
directions;
drain well and set aside.
Cook noodles
according
to
directions; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour,
stirring
until smooth.
Cook
minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook
over
medium heat, stirring
constantly until thick and
bubbly.
Stir
in salt and pepper.
Stir 1/2 cup of white sauce
into
the spinach.
Spoon spinach mix into a greased
baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix noodles and 1/2 cup of white sauce and spoon over
cheese. Spoon
remaining
white
sauce
over
noodles. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Put the rest into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg; beat until light and smooth.
Spread over layer just cooked. Sprinkle reserved cake mix over top.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top to serve.

title: luscious coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in large microwave mixing bowl.
Gradually add the milk, mixing well.
Microwave 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Remove from oven and stir small amount of hot mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks; then blend egg yolk mixture into hot milk mixture.
Microwave 2 more minutes, stirring once.
Remove from oven.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in coconut. Pour into pastry shell.
Spread meringue on top of pie and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled. (This is a family favorite.)

title: skillet chicken and potatoes(makes 2 large servings; low-fat)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add the potatoes and ground meat and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Transfer to a plate and set aside.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour peaches into pan.
Pour mixture over peaches and bake in 375° oven until golden brown.

title: pink lemonade pies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into crusts.
Makes 2 pretty pies.

title: oven stew for a large crowd
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Do not brown meat. Cover and bake 7 hours at 250°, or until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients except baking soda.
Cook until hard ball stage or 280°.
Add peanuts.
Continue to cook until 305° or crack stage.
Turn fire off and add baking soda.
Stir until mixed well and pour out on buttered cookie sheet and spread as thin as possible.
Cool and break.

title: chess pie
directions: Add sugar to creamed butter, blend well.
Add eggs, beat in mixer for about 10 minutes.
Add dates, raisins, and nuts.
Bake in pie shell at 425 degrees for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325 for 30 minutes.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl or bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken and coat all pieces well. Pour melted butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place chicken, skin side up, in dish on top of butter; roll over once, with skin side up again. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Drain excess liquid, but do not leave totally dry. Combine rest of ingredients together and mix well. Pour over chicken and bake an additional 45 minutes. Baste with drippings in pan about every 10 minutes during cooking time. Serves 4 to 6.

title: onion cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, combine the milk, egg and butter.
Add biscuit mix, 1/2 cup cheese and onion.
Spoon into six greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle with the poppy seeds and remaining cheese.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack. Makes 6 biscuits.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Boil boiling water, oleo, shortening and cocoa.
Bring to rolling boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soda, add vanilla just before mixing.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: citrus cabbage slaw
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients together. In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Toss into cabbage mixture. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Toss again before serving.

title: easy sticky bun cake
directions: The night before, spray Bundt pan with cooking spray.
Layer 1/2 cup raisins and/or nuts, bag of frozen rolls and melted butter.
Mix dry pudding (do not cook), brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top.
Let raise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbs form.
Combine milk, vanilla and egg; stir into flour until moistened.
Spread dough into 8-inch square baking pan.
Arrange peaches in rows, pressing lightly into dough.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: salmon divan provencale
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain salmon and reserve liquid.
Add enough milk to reserved liquid to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Flake salmon into large chunks and set aside.
Cook broccoli until almost done.
Drain and arrange in a shallow 8-inch baking dish. Spread salmon over broccoli.
Melt butter in saucepan; add garlic and flour and mix.
Add milk mixture and stir until bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Drain tomatoes and cut into chunks. Add to sauce and pour over salmon.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: backpack cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and honey; add eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Stir in oats, flour and milk powder; blend thoroughly.
Add raisins and nuts.
Fold in bran flakes.
Drop by tablespoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake 12 minutes until edges are slightly browned. These cookies freeze well, travel well and are so healthy you can feed them to the kids for breakfast.

title: nut ball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix salt and vanilla to flour.
Mix flour, sugar and nuts slowly (leave 1 cup of chopped nuts for rolling balls).
Drop mixture on ungreased pan.
Cook 25 minutes. After cooking, roll cookie balls in powdered sugar.

title: vegetarian eggplant lasagna
directions: Dredge eggplant in flour and lightly saute both sides in skillet with hot olive oil.
Line casserole dish with eggplant slices.
Layer with Mozzarella and sprinkling of grated Parmesan, then pasta, then tomato sauce.
(Try slicing a few ripe plum tomatoes in with the sauce when they're in season, or add simmered onion slices or well drained cooked spinach.)
Alternate layers ending with Mozzarella and Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes until cheese and sauce bubble and eggplant is cooked through.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pluck-it coffee cake
directions: Cut rolls into 3 pieces each and place in large mixing bowl. Melt oleo and mix with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour mixture over rolls, coating each piece well.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate.

title: blueberry oat coffeecake
directions: Grease
and
flour
a
9-inch
cake pan.
Combine blueberries and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cream margarine with sugar. Beat egg well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and cardamon; stir into creamed mixture, alternately with yogurt. Spoon carefully over blueberries and sugar in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes when done. Serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour strawberries into pie shell.
Combine in a saucepan water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over strawberries while still hot.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: italian oven cheese chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients except the last 3 ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring at 30 minutes.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Cook for 10 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
May be frozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and dates; blend well.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs on high until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is double in volume.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water and vanilla to egg mixture, beating on low speed just until combined.
Immediately pour into greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: mom's sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, eggs, vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
This can be topped with miniature marshmallows if desired.

title: country cajun shrimp bread
directions: Cut shrimp into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook shrimp and onion in margarine over medium heat for 5 minutes or until opaque.
Cut French bread loaf in half lengthwise.
Reserve one half for another use.
Hollow the center of bread with fork to form a 1/2-inch thick shell.
Break any big pieces of scooped out bread into crumbs.
Place crumbs and shell on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine crumbs, shrimp mixture, cajun seasoning, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into the hollowed loaf. Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: creole fillets
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over moderately low heat (225°).
Add celery, green pepper and onion to skillet.
Cook until onion is lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, rice, oregano, salt and black pepper into skillet.
Cook, covered 10 minutes.
Arrange fish over sauce mixture.
Cook with a cover for 10 to 15 minutes until rice is tender and fish can be flaked easily.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Combine fruits and nuts.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter well.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Beat in vanilla and citrus rind.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add 1/4 of dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Continue procedure; beat well after each addition.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil; add jello.
Cool.
Whip with electric mixer.
Whip in Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Place in mold.
Chill.
Takes about 25 minutes to prepare.

title: in-a-hurry-chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken in microwave 6 minutes or until done.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
Mix chicken and remaining ingredients in large stew pot.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken pieces in dish.
Mix lemon juice and water; pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Sprinkle front and back of chicken heavily with lemon pepper seasoning.
Cut margarine; place on chicken pieces.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Spoon juice over chicken before serving.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a small bowl in the order given. Stir with a slotted spoon until the batter is smooth.
It should be lumpy only because of cheese and pepperoni.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is firm.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: pretzel letters
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Add flour and knead for 6 minutes.
Cover the dough and let it rise in a greased pan until it doubles in size.
Divide the dough into 12 sections.
Roll each section into long snake-like pieces. Form the pieces into letters.

title: mexican style peppers
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add seasoning mix according to package directions; set aside.
In a saucepan, cover and cook tomatoes and rice until tender. Rice cooks by using tomato liquid.
Set aside. Boil peppers until soft.
Combine all ingredients except cheese. Fill a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with mixture and top with cheese.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted.
Great do ahead recipe.
Just re-warm in oven when ready to use.

title: pepper relish
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients together in saucepan.
Stir until smooth.

title: chicken mornay for 2
directions: Coat chicken breasts with 1/2 cup flour combined with 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and ginger.
Shake in paper bag to coat. Brown on all sides in 1/2 cup butter in heavy frypan.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 30 to 45 minutes or until tender (a little water may be added if necessary).

title: grilled chicken breast(low-fat)
directions: Put breasts in glass baking dish in one layer.
Beat all ingredients in a small bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 hours.
Turn once during that time. Preheat broiler.
Remove breasts from the marinade and broil 4 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: mike's mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and save for other uses.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and brush over mushroom caps, coating thoroughly.
Stir together remaining 4 tablespoons butter, garlic and cheese until blended.
Stir in wine, soy sauce and crumbs until well blended.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Brown bacon, chopped small, with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, Cheddar cheese and sugar.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Cook spaghetti; drain. Add 2/3 of sauce.
Pour in casserole dish.
Spoon remainder of sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (grated).
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is hot through.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together. Mix into creamed mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes (just until edges look brown, center will remain soft, baking too long will make cookies crisp).

title: tortellini pasta
directions: Cook tortellini until done.
Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture onto bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Blend eggs, Minute Maid lemon juice and remaining flour and sugar.
Pour over pastry crust.
Bake 15 minutes more or until set. Cool slightly.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cool completely. Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Sift the next 4 dry ingredients together.
Mix buttermilk with bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Add alternately the flour and milk mixture to the sugar and oleo.
Pour into 2 round 8 or 9-inch pans (greased) or a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until done in the center.
Cool.
Decorate with cream cheese frosting and banana slices.
May sprinkle sugar in bottom of pan instead of flour.

title: grandma ensinger's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and flour.
Then add eggs, milk and butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until firm.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in bag. Moisten potatoes with water; add a few at a time to bag.
Shake, coating thoroughly.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan; place potatoes in casserole as taken from bag.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, turning once.

title: almond ham roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham.
Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each slice of ham and roll up jelly fashion.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze up to 1 month.
When ready to serve, thaw and cut rolls into 3/4-inch slices.

title: creole chicken and shrimp with linguine
directions: In a large frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter and 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt, black pepper and cayenne. Saute about 3 minutes, until chicken turns opaque and shrimp turns pink.
Remove and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium and add remaining butter and oil.
Add onion and saute until softened. Add green pepper and garlic and cook until pepper is crisp-tender. Add tomato, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Return shrimp and chicken to pan; mix well and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over linguine or rice.

title: the best brownies ever("you'll never use a mix again.")
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate.
Add the eggs and mix well. Add sugar, salt, vanilla and flour.
Mix. Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan.
Pour in batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish. Peel and slice potatoes very thin. Place potatoes in dish with melted margarine. Add salt and pepper. Stir so all potatoes are covered with butter. Combine grated cheese and corn flakes in a Ziploc bag and shake. Pour on top of potatoes. Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cover with foil to keep cheese from burning and remove foil the last few minutes of baking.

title: winter jam
directions: Cook apricots in the syrup until soft.
Add the orange and lemon juice, sugar and the pineapple.
Cook over low heat in a heavy pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
About 5 minutes before done, add the diced maraschino cherries.
Pour into sterilized jars and process. Makes about 7 jelly jars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
and
lima
beans
according
to package directions;
drain and gently mix together.
Spray long casserole dish
with
Pam and begin layering broccoli, lima beans, mushroom soup,
sour
cream,
dry mushroom onion soup mix and water chestnuts.
Melt margarine; mix with Rice Krispies.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french banana cream pie
directions: Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Add milk to pudding and add liqueur.
Beat until thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Fold into whipped cream.
Add bananas alternately in shell with filling.
Make sure bananas are covered with cream mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: danish pastry
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 of the dough on small cookie sheet.
Spread pie filling over dough and drop remaining dough by teaspoon over filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until brown.
Drizzle icing made from powdered sugar.

title: bermuda salad
directions: Cook beans until crisp-tender, drain, rinse and drain again. Cool.
Place beans and onions on dish. Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over vegetables. Crumble egg and sprinkle over top when ready to serve.

title: cranberry apple punch
directions: Steep tea bags in hot water; add sugar while hot and then allow it to cool.
Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ice ring.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
May be fixed ahead of time and put in fridge or freezer.

title: ants on a log
directions: Spread peanut butter or cream cheese on each celery section. Place raisins (ants) on top of each celery log.
Eat quickly before the ants crawl away.
Pretzel logs can be substituted for celery sections.

title: pork and rice chinese
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart ovenware casserole, place salad oil and rice. Stir to coat rice with oil.
Cook in microwave oven 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until rice becomes a golden brown.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring to mix.
Remove from heat and gradually blend in milk and set aside.
In bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell that has been coated with a small amount of sugar and flour.
Combine pecans and coconut and sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cocktail sauce.
Beat well with electric mixer and chill several hours.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat all together about 1 minute.
Makes about 8 waffles.

title: chocolate snack cakes
directions: Mix together and drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown the
meat.
Drain.
Add onion. Cook until tender. Stir in	tomato paste, water, salt and garlic powder. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: catalina dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer not blender.
Let stand 24 hours before using to blend flavors.
Will keep for up to a week in refrigerator.

title: grandma's apple butter
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Layer apples in a slow cooker till full.
Add the cinnamon stick and star anise.
Do not add water. Cook on low 9 hours with lid on.
Remove lid and cook 6 hour longer.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Cut chicken in one-inch pieces.
Mix soy sauce, garlic powder, sugar, salt, ginger and ground pepper.
Marinate chicken one hour in sauce mixture in refrigerator.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Stir in milk gradually.
Sprinkle nutmeg over batter. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie shell is good and brown and mixture is set.
Remove from oven.
Cool for 1 hour. Serve.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pull easy open tab.
Place biscuits 1/4-inch apart in two rows on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and serve hot.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: daisy's spicy chicken enchiladas
directions: With just enough water to cover top, boil chicken breasts and 1/2 teaspoon pepper (optional) with chilies and onion until all water is boiled out; shred chicken.
Pour mixture into hot, lightly oiled skillet and let simmer over very low heat while preparing rest of ingredients.
Be sure to keep tossed to keep from burning.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel and picante.
Bring to boil (careful not to let scorch).
Dip each tortilla in hot oil to soften, then into soup mixture.
Lay on baking sheet.
Top with chicken and roll up.
Pour remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni dish
directions: Cook macaroni by directions.
When done, divide.
Melt Cheddar cheese and oleo in milk; put in casserole dish.
Place in oven and brown.
Take the other half of macaroni and add 1 can of tomatoes, onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper, a pinch of sugar and oleo or bacon grease.
Cook for about 10 minutes on top of stove, then eat.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Put into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curried chicken
directions: Optional:
Chicken can be marinated with curry powder and salt overnight in refrigerator.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine sugar and syrup with water in heavy pan.
Stir and heat to boiling over medium heat.
Boil without stirring to 240°. Beat egg whites stiff and slowly pour syrup into beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat to spreading consistency.

title: cranberry rice dessert
directions: Combine rice and cranberry sauce.
Fold in whipped cream and diced marshmallows.
Spoon into individual dishes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar, shortening and egg.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour, soda and salt (sifted together).
Blend in vanilla, rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Very good for a brunch.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve on bun with a slice of cheese, if desired.

title: fruit crumb bars
directions: In
a
mixing
bowl,
stir
together flour, oats, brown sugar and baking soda.
Then stir in melted butter until well combined. Set
cups
of
the oat mixture aside for topper. Pat
the remaining
oat
mixture
into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: german tea rings (2)
directions: In a bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Heat milk, water and margarine until warm. Add to flour mixture. Add eggs and rest of flour.
Place dough in bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
When dough is light, roll out into rectangle 1/4-inch thick. Brush with melted butter. Combine 2/3 white or brown sugar, cinnamon, raisins and chopped nuts.
Spread over dough.
Roll jelly roll fashion. Shape on greased baking sheet into ring.
From the outside, cut through the ring almost all the way through, in 1-inch slices. Turn slices slightly on side and brush with melted fat. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. While still warm, brush with confectioners frosting. Decorate with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: chicken bubba
directions: Sprinkle chicken on all sides with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oil over medium heat on both sides.
Pour off grease. Add carrots, mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Stir and continue cooking about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour evenly over mixture and stir.
Add wine and stir.
Add broth, tomato paste, bay leaf, thyme and mustard; stir.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 5 minutes until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: hot choclate mix
directions: Sift together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. When ready to use, add 4 tsp. of mix to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg.
Stir in water.
Stir in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to mixture.
Stir in raisins, nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Spoon out in drops on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 60.

title: almond bark covered cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Cool.
Dip in almond bark.

title: pumpkin patch pound cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin and almond extract; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Tap gently to remove air bubbles.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and boil 1 minute in salt water.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add sugar and seeds.
Squeeze cabbage.
Add carrot and pepper.
Add vinegar.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: seafoam (brown sugar) divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour slowly onto the whites of the eggs, beaten with the salt.
Continue to beat until nearly stiff enough to hold its form.
Add the nuts and flavoring; turn onto wax paper or pans.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Mix soup, onions, mushrooms and soy sauce; pour over beans. Sprinkle bacon over bean mixture.
Put into casserole dish; pour bacon fat over beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except paprika in heavy saucepan. Bring to low boil.
Cook until edges of oysters begin to curl. Remove from heat.
Add paprika and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Make pudding as usual.
Add Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Add 1/2 of the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add rest of pudding.
Frost graham crackers to cover and lay on top.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper in rings and mix with carrots.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more.
Will keep for 3 weeks in the refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
Mix with electric mixer.
Cut up mandarin oranges.
Add oranges and pineapple to Jell-O mixture.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: fish parmesan
directions: Spray microwave dish with Pam spray.
Spread thin layer of spaghetti sauce on bottom of dish.
Place fish fillets in single layer on top of spaghetti sauce.
Top with more spaghetti sauce. Cover and microwave for approximately 5 minutes.
Rearrange fillets so all are cooked evenly.
Cook an additional 5 minutes. Continue to rearrange and microwave until fillets are white and tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave 1 minute and serve.
Can be served over spaghetti.

title: aunt rose's cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Add 1 cup cake mix and mix until smooth.
A little at a time, add lemon juice, vanilla and milk, beating between additions.
(Mixture will be liquid.)
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven when crust is a little brown.
Let cool.
Top with fresh or frozen whole strawberries.

title: cough mixture
directions: Boil sugar and water until syrup spins a thread.
Beat white of egg until dry.

Put into a bottle and drop in turpentine. Shake bottle until egg and turpentine have mixed well, then pour in the syrup and shake mixture again thoroughly. Bottle should always be shaken just before the mixture is used. This is a fine remedy for colds, hoarseness and pneumonia coughs.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 45 minutes or longer.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat syrup, sugar, salt, cream and vanilla together.
Add eggs and mix.
Add oats and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Take biscuits and cut each one up into little pieces.
Put in big bowl.
Add melted butter, then sugars.
Last, add cinnamon. Put into a greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions until soft; put through sieve.
Press out the clear juice and save for juice or flavor for gravies, etc. Press and save the thick pulp for the ketchup.
Add salt, oils and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Add sugar, cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon red pepper, if desired.
Cook well and can.
This has a bright red color and is more like commercial ketchup.

title: easy fruit pudding
directions: Spread fruit in an 8-inch square microwavable dish.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts together.
Sprinkle over cake mix and pour melted butter over mixture.
Microwave on High 11 to 13 minutes, rotating dish.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Put nuts in pan first, then all but 6 rolls.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Mix butter and cinnamon together; drizzle over top.
Let rise overnight, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put plate on top and turn out.

title: sugar-free carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter in a large bowl until creamy.
Blend in eggs, pineapple juice concentrate and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in carrots.
Spread batter into a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Bring
to
a rolling boil. Remove from
heat
and cool a few minutes.
Add strawberries. Pour
in baked pie crust and refrigerate.
After pie has set, garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: peanut candy
directions: Use a heavy saucepan or skillet.
Bring first three ingredients to a full boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and peanuts.
Remove from heat.
Set pan in cold water and stir until it thickens.
Pour into butter plate; cut into squares.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat well.
Set aside.
Place bread in a single layer in a shallow dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread; turn slices to coat evenly.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Fry in 2 tablespoons butter, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lace cookies
directions: Add oatmeal, flour, sugar and salt; stir.
Pour hot butter over this and stir.
Add beaten eggs.
Cover pan with foil, do not grease.
Drop onto sheet.
Cook at 325° for 8 minutes.
Watch closely.
Move foil off of pan and let get cold, then remove cookies with spatula.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients, beating vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest about 5 minutes.
Put on oiled baking sheet.
Top with favorite pizza toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shortening bread
directions: Sift flour in
bowl.
Add
sugar.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in
Crisco
with spoon.
Add milk (by this time mixture should look like biscuit dough).
Knead with your hand for 5 minutes.	Shape
into oval shape cakes.
Fry in pan with little Crisco.
Brown on both sides.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Mix in and beat remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour quickly into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: brown rice
directions: Place soups, rice and sprinkle with pepper into 2-quart dish. Stir together.
Place margarine on top, then cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll 1 crescent roll around each apple piece.
Put in buttered dish.
Heat margarine, sugar and orange juice in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over apples.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: mount holly goolash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of vegetables and simmer for a while.
You can also season with basil, garlic or lemon pepper (whatever).
Have fun.
Cook about 20 minutes, until it all smells good.
Pour over wide noodles or whatever.
A little wine included is nice.

title: special occasion salad
directions: Add first 4 ingredients in layers in the order given.
Cover with a light layer of sugar.
Cover completely with mayonnaise. Top with cheese.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour; add baking powder.
Add flour and milk to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Do not preheat oven.
Put in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spicy saimin
directions: Boil 2 cups of water.
Add noodles and broth seasoning until noodles are al dente.
Add in Chinese cabbage, meat and hard part of green onions.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove the noodles to a bowl to avoid overcooking them.
Add the egg to the boiling broth and cook.
Pour the egg and broth mix over the noodles.
Stir in the kochujar right before eating.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sour cream; stir in butter or oleo and corns. Last, add corn muffin mix.
Put in greased 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Roll dough into walnut sized balls. Roll in slightly beaten egg whites, then roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint in each cookie.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground beef in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Pour onion soup mix on top of ground beef, then English peas and then add celery soup on top of peas.
Place Tater Tots on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mama's easy hamburger casserole
directions: Press ground beef evenly into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer the sliced potatoes over the meat and continue layering the rest of the ingredients into the pan in the order given.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until the meat is cooked and the potatoes are soft.
Serve with garlic bread.
It's a one pan meal!

title: easy homemade butter pecan ice cream
directions: In a large bowl stir together milk, beaten egg yolks, maple flavoring and butter pecan flavoring.
Fold in cream, which has been whipped.
Melt 2 teaspoons butter in a small pan.
Add nuts. Cool and stir into other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch foil-lined loaf pan; cover and freeze for 6 hours.
Remove from pan and peel foil; slice or it can be scooped out.

title: chocolate chewie cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough into marble sized pieces and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic.
Add water, sauce and cabbage to hamburger mixture.
Simmer until almost done.
Add beans and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put yeast in cool milk.
Add 2 cups flour.
Let rise until light, then beat in rest of ingredients.
Knead lightly.
Let rise.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from the fruit into a pan and stir in the dry tapioca pudding.
Bring the juice and tapioca pudding to a boil. Cook and stir until thick.
Cool and add to drained fruit. Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing; spread over cheese.
Top with tomatoes; set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small bite size pieces. Add milk and half and half. Stir and let set 10 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost 1 dough.
Cover in a warm, draft-free place so it rises.
Let rise 3 times normal size.
Roll thin into circle or square.
Place layer of ham and pepperoni on dough.
Place chopped Mozzarella on and sprinkle grated cheese.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs together well; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
After allowing to mix well, put children in the bathtub to cool.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Spread onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then turn cake onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper and let cool 10 minutes.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: In large bowl (not aluminum), combine macaroni, tomato, onion, bell pepper, chili pepper, cilantro and garlic.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Toss again before serving. Makes 2 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together thoroughly.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture; beat thoroughly.
Add flavoring; blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: cooky jar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Roll dough out and cut cookie shapes.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: b~b~q sauce
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce, Catalina dressing and soup mix in a saucepan.
Simmer on stove.
Delicious on grilled or baked chicken.

title: whoopee pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: angie's chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with poultry seasoning and sage.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown chicken in margarine with mushrooms and onion.
When chicken is almost fully cooked, add soup and water.
Stir well and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rice and simmer for an additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 3-story dream cake
directions: Mix well flour, oleo and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cool completely.

title: german chocolate turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Spread half of batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: On the crust, layer the bananas.
In a bowl, mix the cream cheese, butter and sugar, then add the pineapple.
Add whipped cream.
Mix well.
Place the mix on the bananas.
Add cherries and pecans, if desired.
Place the pie in the refrigerator for 1 hour, then serve.

title: easy taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain and set aside.
Mix refried beans and 1 can tomato sauce in saucepan; heat over low heat.
Set aside.
Grate cheese.
Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan, beginning with ground beef.
Next, add layer of corn chips, then refried beans, then cheese.
Continue layers, topping off with cheese.
Pour can of tomato sauce over top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread thinly on tortilla shell.
Layer pimentos, green chilies and black olives on top. Roll shell tightly and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut in 1/4-inch pieces and dip in salsa.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Remove shells from peanuts to make 2 cups of nuts.

Process nuts in an electric blender until powdery, then gradually add up to 1/4 cup of peanut or safflower oil, one tablespoon at a time, blending completely. Stop blender from time to time to push the peanuts into the center.
When the peanut butter is the consistency you like, stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt and about 1 teaspoon honey to heighten the flavor.
Store in covered container.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Mix together eggs, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients, then cheese, spinach (squeeze dry) and seasoning.
Bake in 3-quart ovenproof dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 48 squares.

title: curried chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in oil.
Remove from skillet and drain. Leave crumbs; add 2 tablespoons oil.
Add diced onion to oil and cook until yellow.
Add uncooked rice and curry powder.
Stir well.
Add chicken broth and salt to taste.
Place in a casserole dish and lay chicken on top of rice.
Cover.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes or until rice is done.

title: branham's chicken bog(southern style)
directions: Bring to a boil the water and onion soup.
Add sausage and chicken.
When chicken is done, remove, debone, cut into small pieces and return to broth.
Add rice and return to boil.
Cook on medium heat until rice is done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together. Add 3 to 4 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Chill before serving.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable stuffed shells
directions: In a saucepan, cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the vinegar, salad oil, sugar, pepper, onion, celery seed and mustard seed; mix well.
Stir in the drained vegetables.
Cover and chill. Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain and chill.
Drain vegetable mixture and spoon into shells.
Arrange stuffed shells on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.
Enjoy!

title: chicken asparagus rolls
directions: Combine garlic powder, rosemary and salt; sprinkle over chicken.
Lay 1/2 slice cheese on each piece of chicken.
Top with 4 asparagus spears.
Fold long edges of chicken breast over the cheese and asparagus; secure with wooden pick.
Sprinkle chicken rolls with paprika.
Place seam down in 12 x 8-inch baking dish; cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes; turn and rearrange chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; cover and microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes until chicken is opaque and tender.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, onions and celery until fine. Cover with boiling water. Let set for 5 minutes, then drain. Mix together the remaining ingredients, making sure sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Add ground vegetables and simmer for 12 minutes. Spoon into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: punch
directions: Freeze some of the mixture in a ring and some for slush. Add ginger ale (chilled) as you serve the punch in proportions as you like.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon together in large bowl. Add oil, apples and vanilla.
Beat by hand the egg yolks until light in color. Add slowly the sugar, continually to beat. Fold in egg whites. Add nuts and raisins. Pour in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients. Pour over cereal. Stir gently until coated. Pour powdered sugar in large plastic container. Add cereal mixture. Cover with lid and shake until coated with powdered sugar.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients well, but lightly.
Form into small egg shaped patties and fry in deep fat for 7 or 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wassail
directions: Combine cider, orange juice and lemonade, and brown sugar in crock pot.
Mix well.
Place nutmeg, cloves, and allspice in cheesecloth bag or spice ball.
Add to juices in crock pot.
Cover and cook on low 2 - 8 hours.
Float orange slices and cinnamon stick on top when done.

title: pineapple cheese dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, sugar, softened margarine and nuts.
Press into 11 x 7-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until lightly tanned.
Do not overbake.
When cooled, spread with cream cheese mixture.

title: maple syrup(save your old syrup bottles.)
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar. Add maple flavoring. Let liquid cool before pouring into your old bottle. Tastes the same for a lot less cost. Makes 1 pint.

title: cheese straws
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in other ingredients.
Put dough in a cookie press; use star blade.
Place long strips on cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375° until brown.
Do not overcook.

title: ground turkey loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a lightly greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Marinate overnight, stirring once or twice.
Drain off juice before serving.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: spicy walnut chews(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spice.
In large bowl, cream together margarine and honey.
Add eggs; blend in applesauce and then molasses.
Stir in flour mixture and oats, blending well.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto oiled baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand on cookie sheet 5 minutes and then place on rack.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries (unthawed), breaking up with a fork.
Pour into cooled pie shell. Chill until completely set.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt thoroughly.
Bring milk to scalding and add dry ingredients gradually, stirring often, until thick, about 15 minutes.
Add butter and egg yolks; cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell and cover with meringue.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Join 2 crescent rolls at perforated seams to form a square. Place about 1/2 of the mixture in middle of the square and bring ends together to form a large puff. Coat top of puff with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili con-carne
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet with butter and minced onions. Drain grease.
Add beans and simmer 20 minutes.
If higher seasoning is desired, add a dash or two of hot sauce or Tabasco sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla; fold in the cocoa and oats.
Drop from a tablespoon onto waxed paper or buttered dish.
Let cool.
No baking necessary.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into small pieces.
Combine broccoli, onion, bacon bits and cheese in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; stir well.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over broccoli mixture and toss.
Allow salad to marinate about 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Precook chicken breast and broccoli. Place broccoli in casserole dish; layer chicken over it. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese with hamburger
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook box of macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add to beef and spaghetti sauce.

title: fraiche a'la cream
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Mix with "creme fraiche" (recipe follows) and refrigerate until serving time.
Looks pretty in champagne glasses with sprig of mint.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place rolls into two 9-inch pie pans, points of rolls toward center of pans. Layer sausage and potatoes. Add onions and peppers, if you like. Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper and pour over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, cream margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 1 hour.
Best served warm.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese spread and picante sauce in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese spread is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix with milk. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate until cold.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems very fine. Saute in butter with the garlic about two minutes over medium heat.
Add bacon, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and wine.
Stuff raw mushroom caps.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together.
Add the remaining ingredients together.
Put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Mix with butter, vanilla, sugar, eggs and dates.
Pour in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Fold ends into center so a "bundle" is formed; wrap with 1/2 piece of bacon.
Set wrapped breasts into a bed of 2 to 3 slices of dried beef. Arrange beef, chicken and bacon bundles in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together, then pour over bundles, making sure all are covered well with mixture.
Bake in a slow oven (250° to 300°), uncovered, for 3 hours.
Chicken will be very tender and moist.
Serve as a beef-chicken bundle with rice. The juice-gravy produced is great on rice and also on the meat. Leftovers freeze well.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Stir together and store in tightly covered container.

title: red cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in lime and 2 1/2 gallons water.
Wash real well and soak 3 hours in cold water.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, alum and red food coloring.
Add enough water to the cucumbers to cover well and simmer 2 hours.
Drain well.
Mix 3 cups vinegar, sugar, red hots, 3 cups water and cinnamon sticks.
Heat until candy and sugar dissolve.
Stir often so candy will not stick to pan.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Pour off liquid each morning for 3 mornings.
Bring to boil and pour liquid back over cucumbers. The 4th morning, put pan on stove and bring all of it to a boil and put in jars.

title: thunderbolt cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together cocoa, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add flour mixture alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut; turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with your favorite creamy frosting (vanilla or chocolate).

title: cheese spins
directions: This recipe goes with Beef Garden Casserole.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; add margarine and stir, then add corn, soup and cheese.
Bake in a greased dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon-lime congealed salad
directions: It's amazing how many folks who don't usually eat broccoli or cauliflower enjoy this.

title: easy oriental chicken and noodles
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, broth and soy sauce until smooth and set aside.
Cook noodles in water with seasoning packets.
Drain off liquid and set aside.
In skillet or wok, stir-fry half of the chicken in the oil.
Remove; stir-fry remaining chicken.
Remove and set aside.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Add ginger.
Add cornstarch mixture and chicken to vegetables.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over the noodles.
May add soy sauce to taste.

title: brownie fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate and butter (or margarine); let cool.
Beat eggs and salt until light, add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and creamy.
Fold in melted chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.

title: orange jello salad(lite)
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add Jell-O and pineapple. Chill.
Lay mandarin oranges on top.

title: easy pecan apple pie
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the butter with brown sugar.
When melted, pour in pecan halves.
Pour over pie and return to oven to bake until top bubbles, about 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple really well.
Mix Cool Whip and dry jello with cottage cheese, then add oranges and pineapple. Stir well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: cherry-apple crisp
directions: Layer apple slices in greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread with pie filling.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and granola (also nuts, if you wish).
Add melted margarine and mix.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 50 minutes, until apples are done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet in a casserole dish.
Layer sliced potatoes and sliced onion.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Lay browned chops on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix the butter, sugar and peanut butter together.
Press to desired thickness into little paper candy cups.
Melt the chocolate and pour over the pressed mixture.
Let cool.

title: oriental scallop and noodle soup
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, slice each scallop horizontally in half.
Remove tough stems from spinach and coarsely chop leaves.
Cut peppers into very thin strips.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook pepper strips 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
To skillet with pepper strips, add teriyaki sauce, seasoning packet from one package Oriental-style noodles (reserve other seasoning packet to make soup another day) and 4 cups of water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Add scallops, spinach and noodles.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until noodles are tender and scallops are opaque.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt.
Beat sugar and butter in a large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dates and dissolved baking soda. On low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture.
By hand, stir in nuts.
Chill several hours until firm.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Form dough into 6 rolls, about 10 inches long on a lightly floured surface.
Place 2 rolls 5 inches apart on each prepared baking sheet.
Flatten to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown (longer baking time will produce crisper cookies).
While hot, cut diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Cool on baking sheet 5 minutes. Remove and cool on wire racks.
Makes 60.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine everything except chocolate chips in a bowl working it together until smooth.
Press mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread over mixture.
Refrigerate to firm and cut into squares.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs; spread into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly. Yield: about 6 servings.

title: tater tots
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper and drain. Combine all ingredients and top with Tater Tots and bake until bubbly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Cook on medium heat until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop with spoon onto waxed paper until set.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in applesauce. Sift together the flour, soda, salt and nutmeg, then add to the shortening mixture.
You may want to add 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop round teaspoons about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until, when lightly touched with finger, no imprint remains at 400°, about 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: layered meat loaf
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Place half of mixture in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Add layer of stuffing.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Top with cheese slices if desired and return to oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: party punch
directions: Mix punch, soda and frozen lemonade together until concentrate is melted.
Add strawberries and orange sherbet.
Enjoy!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil and spread with a heavy coat of butter.
Spray saucepan and spoon with Pam cooking spray.
Prepare hot soapy dish water in sink.

title: catsup
directions: Cook tomatoes, peppers and garlic until tender; press through sieve.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices to tomato pulp, and cook rapidly for abut 45 minutes until thick.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Cover and seal.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic salt, salt and pepper in saucepan, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add celery, onion, beans, cabbage, tomatoes, water and bouillon cubes; mix well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: stir-fry beef with chile and mint(servings:  6)
directions: In stir-fry skillet, heat vegetable oil.
Saute garlic and green onion.
Add peppers and beef, cooking on high heat very quickly.
Drain any remaining oil.
Add fish sauce and honey; bring to bubble.
Add basil and mint.
Remove from heat.
Serve over rice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Take can of applesauce and add baking soda.
Heat to very hot; set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add applesauce mix, then gradually add oil, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased angel food pan.

title: tallerine
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper and chili powder in large pan such as a Dutch oven.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Add cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
This makes a large amount and it freezes well. Just thaw and reheat.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts or appears bubbly.

title: cream cheese lemon squares
directions: Mix baking mix, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press in bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of glass dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium, rotating dish 1/2 turn every 2 minutes, until dry to touch, 6 to 10 minutes.
Place on heatproof surface.

title: diabetic angel delight
directions: Slice cake in two layers.
On each layer spread desired thickness of peanut butter, sliced bananas and whip cream in order.
Ice cake with remaining whipped cream when second layer is placed over first layer.
Keep covered and refrigerated.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine in mixing bowl, cream cheese, egg 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt, beat well.
Stir in chocolate pieces, set aside. Sift flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt into mixing bowl, combine water, cooking oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill muffin cups 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top each with heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: german slaw
