directions: In a large bowl combine shredded cabbage, onion and peppers. In a saucepan bring to a rolling boil the vinegar, seeds, salt and sugar.
Pour heated mixture over vegetables and cool as quickly as possible in the refrigerator.
Let stand overnight to improve flavor.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix all together and put in punch bowl. Add little yellow orange food coloring, if desired. Garnish with lemon and orange slices on top.

title: sue's chicken supreme
directions: Place chipped beef in bottom of baking dish. Wrap chicken with bacon strips. Place over beef in baking dish. Mix soup and sour cream together. Pour over chicken. Cover completely. Bake 3 hours at 275°. Serve over rice.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in fondue pot and keep hot. Toast English muffins or French bread.
Cut into cubes.
Dip with fondue forks.

title: rollemups
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder. Add the butter and mix to a soft dough with the egg and milk. Roll half an inch thick on a floured board; sprinkle with the brown sugar and cinnamon and roll into a long roll. Press the edges together closely and cut into 3/4-inch slices with a sharp knife. Lay cut side down on a greased pan. Bake about 20 minutes in a quick oven (400°). Cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Flour and brown meat.
Put in kettle and add rest of ingredients except the sour cream.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Cool slightly and add sour cream.
Can be thickened with cornstarch if necessary.

title: lone star texas barbecue
directions: Brown beef in oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Simmer until soft.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin; mix well.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon;
gradually add to the pumpkin mixture.
Bake in greased and floured Texas sheet cake pan 20-25 minutes.
For frosting, beat cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and milk; ice cooled cake.

title: colonial peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into buttered pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut.

title: a passel of punch
directions: Combine
juices,
sugar
and mint leaves.
Chill several hours and
strain.
Pour over large cake of ice in punch bowl. Slowly pour down side of bowl ginger ale and carbonated water. Add strawberries;
float thin slices of lemon and lime.
Makes about 60 servings.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Place apples in 10-inch well greased pie pan. Cover with 1/4 cup sugar. Cream together butter and remaining sugar.
Add eggs and mix. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix with creamed mixture. Spread over fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in large skillet and cook macaroni, onions and green pepper in meat fat until macaroni is yellow.
Return meat to skillet along with tomato sauce, sugar, pepper, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit your taste.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom and set aside.
Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over the nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
While baking, make the glaze.

title: rice krispies balls
directions: Empty the Rice Krispies into a large bowl and set aside.
In microwave, melt the caramels, butter and milk in a large bowl. Mix well.
With tongs, dip a marshmallow into caramel mixture, then roll in the Rice Krispies.
Press Krispies into caramel dipped marshmallow with your hands.
Place on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
You must keep heating caramel to keep it thin.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach per directions.
Drain well.
Add onion soup mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix in ice cream freezer.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach and eggs.
Add cottage cheese and bake at 350° until brown on top, approximately 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except the 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans. Roll into a ball. Roll the cheese ball in the finely chopped pecans. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: dr. pepper jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot Dr. Pepper.
Add raspberries.
Stirring, add pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Chill until firm.
Mix together sour cream, marshmallows, sugar and lemon juice.
Unmold salad and top with sour cream mixture.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jeannine's quick and easy mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together, but the cheese.
Cook in an iron skillet. This is also very good cooked in cornbread stick pans.
I spray them with Pam and fill half full of the mixture and sprinkle the cheese in the middle.
Add more mixture on top.
Cook in a 375° or 400° oven until very brown.
This helps keep from sticking.
If you use an iron skillet to cook, be sure you cook at least an hour, because it will not get done on inside.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls flat on cookie sheet and press together.
Bake according to package, but do 10 minutes, not 12 so it is not brown. Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on cool crust.
Cut up veggies and drop on and put cheese on last.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine
cranberries, apples and orange; mix well.
Add remaining.
Chill. Store
in
airtight container in refrigerator. Makes 1 quart.

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Begin 6 hours or up to 1 week ahead.
Heat water and butter until very warm, 120 to 130°.
Butter does not have to melt.

In a large mixing bowl, mix sugar, salt, yeast and 2 1/4 cups flour. With a mixer at low speed, gradually add liquid to dry ingredients. Add egg and beat at medium speed 2 minutes occasionally scraping bowl with a rubber spatula.
Beat in 3/4 cup flour or enough to make a stiff batter.
Continue beating 2 minutes.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Place in a large, greased bowl turning over to grease top.
Cover with towel and place in a warm place.
Let rise double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough.
Turn dough over and brush with oil.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Punch down dough occasionally.
About 2 1/2 hours before serving, grease pan and cut dough into 30 equal pieces. Shape into balls and place in pan.
Cover with towel and place in a warm area.
Let double; preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 30 rolls.

title: skillet creamed corn
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon and drain on paper towels, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon; set aside. Saut onion and garlic in hot drippings 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in corn; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until golden. Remove from heat. Cook flour in a large clean skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine equal parts of mayonnaise and sour cream (light or fat free is fine).
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Amounts of chicken and fruit are not critical, but this combination of flavors is a delicious summertime quick meal.
Excellent way to use leftover chicken! Can be served on lettuce leaves.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in air tight container.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, Wesson oil, salt and pepper. Heat and pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Put sugar, flour, and cornmeal in large bowl; toss with fork. Add eggs, melted butter, milk, lemon rind, and lemon juice. Beat until blended. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 35-45 minutes. No topping is necessary; cornmeal and lemon rind rise to top of pie during baking to form a crust.

title: cherry whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes; cool.
Soften cream cheese; add mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with shredded veggies and cheese.
Cut in squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: moma's beef stew
directions: Boil stew meat for about 2 hours, then add mixed vegetables, stewed tomatoes, corn, pepper, salt and green beans.
Let boil for 35 minutes, then add tomato paste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the Roni and let them get tender.
By the time the Roni is tender, the stew will be done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into a long roll and wrap in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep a week or two and you can cook as you need them.
To cook, slice into 1/4 inch slices and bake at 350 degrees to 375 degrees for about ten minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread in greased pan and bake for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: sea dream salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce and mayonnaise.
Garnish with curry powder.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Sprinkle rice on bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken pieces on rice.
Mix mushroom soup, celery soup and Lipton soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Boil and mash yams.
Add butter, spices and sugar to yams.
Beat until light and smooth.
Beat egg yolks until light and add.
Stir in juice, rind and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until pie puffs up and is firm in middle.
Cool.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and make into patties.
Cook in hot oil over medium heat.
May be frozen and fried later.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Put first 6 ingredients together and boil; cool and put in pie crust.
Add 6 sliced bananas on top; nuts and cream on top.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Split zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out center flesh, leaving shell 1/2 inch thick.
Cook shells in microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes, covered.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.

title: mrs. vinson's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla in medium sized bowl.
Add flour to make dough.
Roll out thin. Cut with biscuit cutter and bake 8 minutes (be sure to time). When bottoms get brown, put oven on broil.
Watch closely to brown tops (only takes a minute).

title: smokey baked beans
directions: In large skillet fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and crumble.
Combine pork and beans, onion, garlic, barbecue sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and mustard.
Mix in crumbled bacon and franks.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: good chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into this and put in hot pan you have put the oil in.
Mix wet ingredients, add to browned meat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked trout
directions: May use zucchini, artichoke hearts, carrots, sauteed mushrooms and green pepper rings.

title: roast beef slumgullion
directions: In large skillet, mix green pepper, onion, catsup, chili powder and sugar.
Add diced beef to mixture.
Cook on low heat until onion and pepper get tender.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Serve over toast or buns.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes and onion in a baking dish. Add the butter, milk, salt and pepper. Place the pork chops on the top, add salt and pepper and bake at 350°f. 180°c. or gas mark 4 for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box; add 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
Put half of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over warm cake; add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over top and bake 15 or 20 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: dog cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine oats, margarine and water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour; mix well.
Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing well to form a stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead in remaining flour until no longer sticky.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with bite size cookie cutters.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Store loosely covered.

title: chicken cha-cha-cha
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle prepared stuffing over all.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare raw apples which have been peeled and chopped fine. Sift dry ingredients together; set aside. Beat eggs well; add sugar and salad oil. Cream together. Add dry ingredients and mix until well blended. Fold in chopped apples and nuts. (If this is too thick, add a little milk.) Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook macaroni, drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Stir jelly and chili sauce together in pot.
Drop in shaped meat balls.
Simmer in covered pot until meat balls are done. Serve hot.

title: carol brown's white chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
On low speed, add flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.

title: baked ham omelet
directions: Shred cheese.
Dice ham and cook briefly in 1/2 of butter. Sift flour with baking powder.
Beat eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add Tabasco.
Stir in flour, ham, cheese and cottage cheese.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Blend in oats; add chopped nuts and dates.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(You may substitute chocolate chips, raisins or dried apricots.) Yields 5 dozen.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, then add all ingredients.
Let rise in warm place until double in size, knead down and make into rolls.
Place in lightly greased pan.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400°.

title: chili salsa dip
directions: Combine ingredients in sequence of order in a large mixing bowl using a "wooden spoon" or noncaustic weapon.

title: curried chicken
directions: Saute chicken, onions and bell pepper until chicken is done and vegetables are limp.
Stir in sour cream and then add curry paste.
Delicious served over cooked rice.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar, flour, and cornmeal.
Stir to mix. Add the eggs. Beat well. Add the butter, lemon juice, lemon rind and milk. Beat well. Pour the filling into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until the filling is set in the center.
Remove from the oven and cool slightly before slicing.

title: peanut butter cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, fruit juice and fructose.
Add egg and blend well.
Mix dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.
Roll dough into walnut size balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple(great with ham)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients (will look curdled).
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: favorite beef stew
directions: Sprinkle beef cubes with salt and pepper; coat lightly with flour, shaking off excess.
Brown beef cubes, about half at a time, well on all sides in mixture of butter and oil heated in a large, heavy frying pan or Dutch oven, removing and reserving them as they brown.
When all beef is browned, cook onion in same pan, stirring frequently until soft and lightly browned.
Return beef to pan; mix in carrot, garlic, the 1 teaspoon salt, bay leaves and vegetable juice.
Bring to boiling; cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
With a slotted spoon, remove beef to a warm serving dish and keep warm.
Skim and discard fat from cooking liquid.
Bring to boiling.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over beef.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Put all ingredients except zucchini into a jar and shake well. Slice zucchini into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices and add to brine. Refrigerate 5 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator 1 week.

title: candied sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Layer sweet potatoes.
Spread apple pie filling over potatoes.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave garlic butter vegetables
directions: On a large microwave-safe platter, arrange broccoli and cauliflower around outer edge.
Sprinkle with water.
Cover with plastic wrap, leaving one edge open to vent.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Pour all into a large pot and add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with cornbread or biscuits.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice and next 4 ingredients. Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until mixture is moistened.
Gently fold in berries.
Put in muffin tins coated with vegetable oil.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar evenly over muffins.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden.

title: shrimp elegante
directions: Grease cold frypan on bottom and sides with shortening. This will make a thick coat of grease. In a small bowl, mix biscuit mix and milk together. Spread dough evenly in frypan. Arrange sausages and mushroom caps on dough and top evenly with tomato paste, then cheese and sprinkle with oregano. Cover. Turn control dial to 325° and bake until done.

title: cranberry souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add mayonnaise and beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, pinch of salt and cinnamon. Chill until slightly firm. Beat until fluffy.
Use fork to break up cranberries in can. Fold into gelatin mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12 or more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients (except for 1 cup nuts).
Shape into ball and roll in reserved pecans.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, mushrooms, celery, onion soup and chicken broth in 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Add water; mix well.
Arrange chicken pieces skin side up over rice.
Sprinkle with salt.
Melt butter and brush over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
After 45 minutes, remove foil.
Add 1/2 cup more water if rice is beginning to get dry.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly brown sugar, shortening, eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Then add oats, dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian meat pie
directions: First brown hamburger and onion.
Then add the 2 cans of tomato sauce and the dry spaghetti sauce mix.
Pour meat mixture in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Combine sour cream and mozzarella cheese.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Spread crescent rolls over cheese mixture.
Top with 2 Tbsp melted butter and parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: chili queso
directions: Heat chili and cheese until mixture is smooth and hot; add onion.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beet salad
directions: Bring juice, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Add jello and let cool.
Add all other ingredients and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Mix in large bowl the chicken, chicken soup, milk and pepper.
Mix stuffing and butter together. Spoon on top and bake for 45 minutes.
Cook, covered, last 20 minutes.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Stir together flour, oats, brown sugar, orange peel and baking soda in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in the melted butter or margarine; mix thoroughly.
Reserve 1 cup of the flour mixture for the topping.
Pat remaining flour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Spread cranberry sauce over baked crust.
Stir nuts into reserved flour mixture.
Sprinkle over cranberry sauce.
Lightly pat flour mixture into sauce.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes more or until top is golden.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Combine powdered sugar and enough milk to make drizzle.
Drizzle over top.
Cut into bars. Makes 24.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until boiling; add and beat flour, sugar, soda, salt, eggs and buttermilk.
Pour into greased 10 1/2 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Frost as soon as removed from oven.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans until dough consistency. Spread dough in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Then using electric mixer, mix cream cheese, 1 cup whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Using electric mixer, mix both puddings, milk and one teaspoon of whipped topping.
Mix until thick, then pour on top of cream cheese layer.
Then spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Boil sugar, syrup, oleo and salt slowly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in soda until light and foamy.
Pour over popped corn; mix thoroughly.
Place in oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: grammy's angel food pie
directions: Soak 1 box of unflavored gelatin in 2 tablespoons of cold water for 10 minutes. Add 1/3 cup of hot water. Let stand until cold. Beat 3 egg whites until stiff. Add 6 tablespoons of sugar. Whip 1/2 pint of whipping cream and fold into egg whites. Add gelatin to mixture. Pour into Oreo pie crust. Refrigerate until set. Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute oil, onion and carrot in pan.
Put 6 cups water and 6 chicken bouillon cubes or chicken broth with fat removed in large pan.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add first mixture, cooked, drained, fine noodles, broccoli (cleaned and chopped) and salt.
Bring to slow boil.
Add garlic salt.
Just before serving add milk and Velveeta cheese.
Makes a large amount and is really good.

title: easy cranberry dessert
directions: Let ground orange, cranberries and sugar stand until dissolved.
Add jello dissolved.
If desired, add nuts, crushed pineapple or apples.
Set.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Pour over top of chicken.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Crush Escort crackers and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave 15 to 20 minutes.

title: e-z barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in a foil-lined baking dish.
Mix equal amounts of Coke and catsup and pour over chicken.
Seal and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes to brown and thicken sauce.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large buttered dish.
Place chicken pieces on top, after they have been dipped in garlic butter.
Bake for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered, in a 350° oven.

title: greek salad
directions: In bottom of large wooden bowl, let garlic and olive oil stand 30 minutes.
Add all ingredients except croutons.
Toss, just before serving.
Add croutons.
Eat, then use breath mints.

title: cream torte
directions: Blend margarine and flour until fluffy.
Add chopped nuts. Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Chill.

title: summertime
directions: Mix well.
Put in French round.
Use the cut-out center for dipping.

title: cherry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients except ginger ale
in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain. Put in large mixing bowl. Add cheese and butter. Mix eggs and milk. Add to macaroni and cheese. Toss until well mixed. Pour mixture into greased dish. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: all day stew
directions: Mix together soup with water/wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready, adjust seasoning if needed. Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Soak okra in buttermilk and egg mixture while the oil gets hot.
Lift up with your hands the okra and put into the corn meal. Coat okra well and using a slotted spoon, put okra into the hot oil.
(Better to use a big pot with oil like deep fryer.)
When the okra is ready it will turn over.
The trick is not to stir the okra nor put too much in the pan at a time.
My Ben eats this vegetable like popcorn!

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix squash, sugar, oil or eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix altogether (don't forget the nuts).
Use two greased and floured cake pans (loaf).
Take out of oven when pick comes out dry. Cakes will not rise too high because they are very moist.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours; on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chop suey
directions: Fry pork and beef fat; drain off excess fat.
Put fried fat in deep pot.
Brown pork; add to fat in deep pot.
Fry beef.
As liquid accumulates, add to big pot.
Next, saute onions.
Mix these with all other ingredients in large pot.
Cook 15 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch, mixed with mushroom juice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice with additional soy sauce.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes and melt slowly in double boiler with milk or cream.
Heat slowly for 30 minutes and then stir well.
Continue over very low heat until all cheese has completely melted.
Add Worcestershire sauce, red pepper and pimientos with juice.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
(Melting of the cheese with the milk or cream in it can be done in the microwave.)

title: potato-egg casserole
directions: Dice cooked potatoes and eggs.
Melt margarine and mix 1 stick with sour cream.
Add to potatoes and eggs and mix.
Mix bread crumbs with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle over potatoes and eggs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas cow patty cookies
directions: Mix all but last 4 ingredients in very large bowl.
Then add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with ice cream scoop.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: herbed lemon barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of a blender; process on high 1 minute.
With blender on high, add oil in a slow, steady stream.
Process 1 minute.
Add basil and thyme; process on low 30 seconds.
Remove 1 cup sauce and chill.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken; cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain and blot off excess sauce.
Brush 1 cup sauce over chicken the last 30 minutes of cooking time.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.

title: onion rice
directions: Melt oleo and add all ingredients to casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey mustard chicken salad
directions: Mix these items; blend with your favorite chicken salad ingredients just prior to serving.

title: quiche(basic)
directions: *Add chopped broccoli or your favorite vegetable.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Combine sugar, molasses, corn syrup and 1/4 cup water.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Raise temperature to medium; cook, stirring often, until hard-ball stage (265° on candy thermometer), 40 to 45 minutes.
Add soda; stir in butter.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased shallow pan.
When cool enough to handle, pull until opaque and lighter in color.
Form into ropes.
With kitchen shears, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in clear plastic wrap. Makes 72.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Cream together molasses, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan for 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Wash and cut the lemons in half, then into paper-thin slices, rind and all. Remove the seeds and put the slices in a glass bowl. Add the sugar and mix well. Cover this and let stand overnight.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dice onion and saute in butter.
Mix in bowl cream of chicken soup, sauteed onions, cooked and drained broccoli, cooked white rice and melted Cheez Whiz.
Spread in casserole dish.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and dice onion and green pepper.
Mix in sugar, vinegar and oil.

title: marge's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar, graham crackers, margarine and peanut butter.
Pat in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and place in warm oven 5 to 10 minutes to melt chips.
Spread the melted chocolate.

title: quick and easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil about 20 minutes or until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture thickens. Add nuts and pour into greased pan (9 x 6 x 2-inch).
When cool, cut into blocks and serve.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Stir until thoroughly combined. Makes 15 cups. For 1 serving, place 1/3 cup cocoa mixture in a cup; add 3/4 cup boiling water. Great to mix and give as a gift.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as per package directions and keep separated between wax paper.
Reserve 10 to 12 slices Mozzarella and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese for top.
In 8-quart foil pan, 17 x 12 x 3-inch, alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Set pan on large baking sheet and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cook and drain sausage slices and arrange with reserved Mozzarella and Parmesan and bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: oven creamed potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes.
In saucepan over very low heat, melt butter. Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper. Slowly stir in milk. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add horseradish and potatoes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly add sugar until stiff and fluffy. Continue beating and add chocolate chips.
With a spoon, put onto a foiled pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and put in hollowed out bottom of French bread.

title: pork balls with ginger
directions: Mix lightly all the ingredients, except the cornstarch and cooking oil.
Shape the mixture into bite size balls; dust with cornstarch.
Heat the cooking oil.
Deep fry the pork balls until they are cooked through.
Serve hot on toothpicks.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together and set aside. Cream butter at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add sugar and cocoa mixture, beating until light and fluffy. Add milk; beat until spreading consistency. Stir in vanilla.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together the hamburger, bacon or ham and onion.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes.
Stir.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Layer cabbage and meat/onion alternately.
Top with one can tomato soup, plus 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy; add salt and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Add more mayonnaise if needed until it is of a spreading consistency.
This spread is very tasty.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna confetti casserole
directions: Bring water to a rapid boil in saucepan. Add macaroni and salt; stir. Boil rapidly, stirring once or twice, for 7 to 10 minutes or to desired tenderness. Drain macaroni into large colander set in kitchen sink. Return macaroni to saucepan. Add margarine, milk and the cheese sauce mix; stir. Add soup, peas, tuna and pimento. Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture is hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: moon shaped cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder, lemon juice and grated rind.
Mix well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured large square pan or jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle top with finely chopped nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut with round cutter in shape of half moon (using only half of the cutter).

title: cherry delight
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Pour in pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pie filling, dot on margarine.
Sprinkle with nuts if you like.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
May be served with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in roasting pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butterscotch pie (fern's)(in honor of broodmare, "kissed mall")
directions: Put in heavy skillet the sugar, the butter and the cream. Boil together for 5 minutes on medium-high until golden brown.

title: minute maid punch(red with fruit)
directions: For Fruit Ice Ring:
Use gelatin (Tupperware) ring and arrange fruit alternately with cherries.
Pour in enough punch to cover. Freeze until firm.
Fill mold with additional punch.
Freeze until solid.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Place pork and beans in a shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add syrup, mustard and catsup.
Stir to blend.
Lay bacon strips across top.
Heat in hot oven at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes or until beans are hot, bubbling and the consistency desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Bring butter, margarine and sugar to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° until golden (7 to 10 minutes). Spread the chocolate chips on the top of this.
Freeze until firm. Break or cut into pieces and store in an airtight tin.

title: white wine punch
directions: *Combine 4 cups sugar and 2 cups water, boiled and cooled.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo and mix in a large dish with salt.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk. Pour over oleo in dish.
Add cherries and sugar to other mixture but don't stir.
Other types of fruit can be used; such as peaches sprinkled with cinnamon.
